   <i> OUR FIRST STORY EXPLORES</i>    

24
00:01:32,493 --> 00:01:35,794
 <i> WHETHER THIS 1940s RECORDING</i>  
   <i> MAY HAVE HELPED CONVICT</i>     

25
00:01:35,863 --> 00:01:39,097
   <i> THE WOMAN ALLEGED TO BE</i>     
         <i> TOKYO ROSE.</i>           

26
00:01:39,166 --> 00:01:42,801
        <i> WORLD WAR II,</i>          
     <i> THE LONELY PACIFIC:</i>       

27
00:01:42,870 --> 00:01:45,971
<i> AS MANY AS 2 MILLION SERVICEMEN</i>
       <i> LISTEN WISTFULLY</i>        

28
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:49,041
    <i> WHILE A WOMAN'S VOICE</i>      
  <i> FLOATS OVER THE AIRWAVES.</i>    

29
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:50,576
     Greetings, everybody.      

30
00:01:50,644 --> 00:01:53,312
This is your number-one enemy,  
   your favorite playmate...    

31
00:01:53,380 --> 00:01:55,514
        <i> THEY CALL HER</i>          
         <i> TOKYO ROSE.</i>           

32
00:01:55,583 --> 00:01:58,050
  <i> MANY G.I.s CONSIDERED HER</i>    
          <i> A GODSEND,</i>           

33
00:01:58,118 --> 00:02:00,519
  <i> A FAMILIAR AMERICAN VOICE</i>    
     <i> KEEPING THEM COMPANY</i>      

34
00:02:00,588 --> 00:02:02,020
        <i> FAR FROM HOME.</i>         

35
00:02:02,089 --> 00:02:04,690
     <i> BUT IN A CELEBRATED</i>       
        <i> POSTWAR TRIAL,</i>         

36
00:02:04,758 --> 00:02:07,826
  <i> PROSECUTORS PORTRAYED HER</i>    
    <i> AS AN AMERICAN DEVIL,</i>      

37
00:02:07,895 --> 00:02:10,495
 <i> A SIREN WHO KNOWINGLY WORKED</i>  
        <i> FOR THE ENEMY,</i>         

38
00:02:10,564 --> 00:02:12,564
 <i> LURING SOLDIERS AND SAILORS,</i>  

39
00:02:12,633 --> 00:02:15,133
       <i> THEN UNDERMINING</i>        
    <i> THEIR FIGHTING SPIRIT.</i>     

40
00:02:15,202 --> 00:02:18,403
      <i> IN 1948, THE WOMAN</i>       
  <i> WHO TWICE SIGNED HER NAME</i>    

41
00:02:18,472 --> 00:02:21,006
    <i> "THE ONE AND ORIGINAL</i>      
         <i> TOKYO ROSE"</i>           

42
00:02:21,075 --> 00:02:24,009
 <i> WAS BROUGHT BACK FROM JAPAN</i>   
    <i> TO FACE A GRAND JURY.</i>      

43
00:02:24,078 --> 00:02:28,113
      <i> THE WAR HAD ENDED,</i>       
<i> BUT HER BATTLE HAD JUST BEGUN.</i> 

44
00:02:28,182 --> 00:02:31,450
        <i> NOW BILL MOORE</i>         
 <i> FROM SUN CITY WEST, ARIZONA,</i>  

45
00:02:31,518 --> 00:02:33,485
<i> HAS AN OBJECT THAT MAY EXPLAIN</i> 

46
00:02:33,554 --> 00:02:36,054
       <i> THE STORY BEHIND</i>        
       <i> HER CONFESSION.</i>         

47
00:02:36,123 --> 00:02:39,358
    MY UNCLE WENT TO JAPAN      
      TO GET TOKYO ROSE.        

48
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:43,795
                HI, YOU'RE BILL?

49
00:02:43,864 --> 00:02:45,330
      SO I HEAR YOU HAVE        
      A RECORD TO SHOW ME.      

50
00:02:45,399 --> 00:02:46,498
          IS THIS IT?           

51
00:02:46,567 --> 00:02:47,699
                YES, THIS IS IT.

52
00:02:47,768 --> 00:02:48,900
WOW, IT'S UNUSUAL.              

53
00:02:48,969 --> 00:02:50,902
THIS MUST BE 16 INCHES ACROSS.  

54
00:02:50,971 --> 00:02:52,270
        SIXTEEN INCHES, I THINK.

55
00:02:52,339 --> 00:02:54,906
<i> SOMEONE'S WRITTEN "TOKYO ROSE"</i> 
        <i> ON THE RECORD.</i>         

56
00:02:54,975 --> 00:02:58,043
<i> BILL FOUND IT WITH HIS MOTHER'S</i>
<i> THINGS AFTER SHE PASSED AWAY,</i>  

57
00:02:58,112 --> 00:03:00,612
       <i> BUT HE BELIEVES</i>         
    <i> IT ORIGINALLY BELONGED</i>     

58
00:03:00,681 --> 00:03:03,815
<i> TO HIS LARGER-THAN-LIFE UNCLE,</i> 
       <i> HARRY BRUNDIDGE.</i>        

59
00:03:03,884 --> 00:03:06,652
          THIS IS MY UNCLE HARRY
          AND MY AUNT JANET.    

60
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:07,753
WHAT DID HE DO?                 

61
00:03:07,821 --> 00:03:09,554
             WELL, HE WAS       
             A WAR CORRESPONDENT

62
00:03:09,623 --> 00:03:13,291
       AND ASSOCIATE EDITOR     
       OF<i> COSMOPOLITAN</i> MAGAZINE.

63
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:15,394
THIS IS YOU, IS THAT RIGHT?     
                       OH, YEAH.

64
00:03:15,462 --> 00:03:17,262
SO WERE YOU OUT                 
IN THE PACIFIC?                 

65
00:03:17,331 --> 00:03:18,864
                      TWO YEARS,

66
00:03:18,932 --> 00:03:22,401
     AND WE USED TO LISTEN      
     TO TOKYO ROSE ALL THE TIME.

67
00:03:22,469 --> 00:03:25,837
<i> BILL HAD HEARD THAT HIS UNCLE</i>  
 <i> MET TOKYO ROSE ON ASSIGNMENT</i>  

68
00:03:25,906 --> 00:03:29,541
    <i> AND BELIEVES HE PLAYED</i>     
<i> A KEY ROLE IN HER PROSECUTION.</i> 

69
00:03:29,610 --> 00:03:32,010
      AFTER THE WAR,            
      HE WENT BACK OVER TO JAPAN

70
00:03:32,079 --> 00:03:34,613
          AND HE GOT TOKYO ROSE,

71
00:03:34,681 --> 00:03:37,282
               BROUGHT HER BACK 
               TO SAN FRANCISCO,

72
00:03:37,351 --> 00:03:39,818
            AND HAD HER INDICTED
            FOR TREASON.        

73
00:03:39,887 --> 00:03:41,820
    <i> BILL THINKS THE RECORD</i>     
      <i> MAY HAVE BEEN USED</i>       

74
00:03:41,889 --> 00:03:43,655
         <i> AS EVIDENCE</i>           
        <i> IN HER TRIAL,</i>          

75
00:03:43,724 --> 00:03:46,258
   <i> BUT HE'S NEVER BEEN ABLE</i>    
<i> TO HEAR WHAT'S ON THE RECORDING</i>

76
00:03:46,326 --> 00:03:49,227
    <i> BECAUSE IT'S TOO LARGE</i>     
<i> TO PLAY ON STANDARD EQUIPMENT.</i> 

77
00:03:49,296 --> 00:03:52,964
ALL I KNOW IS THAT -- OF COURSE,
WHAT I HEARD FROM MY FAMILY,    

78
00:03:53,033 --> 00:03:55,434
              THAT THIS WAS     
              PART OF THE TRIAL.

79
00:03:55,502 --> 00:03:57,602
WHAT EXACTLY WOULD YOU LIKE     
FOR ME TO FIND OUT              

80
00:03:57,671 --> 00:03:58,937
ABOUT YOUR RECORD?              

81
00:03:59,006 --> 00:04:02,307
        I'D LIKE TO FIND OUT    
        WHAT'S ON IT, OF COURSE,

82
00:04:02,376 --> 00:04:05,310
              AND ABOUT MY UNCLE
              IN THE TRIAL.     

83
00:04:05,379 --> 00:04:07,279
I'LL HAVE TO TAKE THIS          
WITH ME, AND I'D LIKE TO TAKE   

84
00:04:07,347 --> 00:04:08,814
THE PHOTOGRAPHS, TOO,           
IF THAT'S OKAY.                 

85
00:04:08,882 --> 00:04:10,081
              OH, YOU CAN, YEAH.

86
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:11,716
       <i> I FOUND A STUDIO</i>        
       <i> WITH A TURNTABLE</i>        

87
00:04:11,785 --> 00:04:13,618
        <i> THAT CAN PLAY</i>          
     <i> THE OVERSIZED DISC.</i>       

88
00:04:13,687 --> 00:04:15,353
   <i> I'M IN LONG ISLAND CITY,</i>    
          <i> NEW YORK,</i>            

89
00:04:15,422 --> 00:04:19,324
    <i> TO MEET AUDIO ENGINEER</i>     
   <i> GUY ROSMARIN AT VIDIPAX.</i>    

90
00:04:19,393 --> 00:04:21,827
OOH, WOW, I HAVEN'T SEEN        
ONE OF THESE IN A WHILE.        

91
00:04:21,895 --> 00:04:23,695
             WHAT IS IT MADE OF?

92
00:04:23,764 --> 00:04:25,530
PROBABLY ALUMINUM-BASED.        

93
00:04:25,599 --> 00:04:27,332
THEY STARTED USING IT AGAIN     
AFTER THE WAR.                  

94
00:04:27,401 --> 00:04:28,900
       YOU COULDN'T USE ALUMINUM
       DURING THE WAR           

95
00:04:28,969 --> 00:04:30,202
        FOR ANYTHING EXCEPT WAR.

96
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:31,870
THAT'S RIGHT.                   

97
00:04:31,939 --> 00:04:33,772
         Female Voice:          
    All right, take it now      
          from five.            

98
00:04:33,841 --> 00:04:37,209
     Tokyo Rose will touch      
American soil in a few moments  

99
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:39,311
 and will immediately be taken  
         into custody.          

100
00:04:39,379 --> 00:04:42,013
 <i> WELL, THIS CERTAINLY DOESN'T</i>  
<i> SOUND LIKE COURTROOM EVIDENCE,</i> 

101
00:04:42,082 --> 00:04:44,850
<i> BUT BILL'S UNCLE IS DEFINITELY</i> 
     <i> PART OF THE ACTION.</i>       

102
00:04:44,918 --> 00:04:48,787
We're fortunate today in having 
two very famous correspondents. 

103
00:04:48,856 --> 00:04:50,622
      Harry Brundidge...        

104
00:04:50,691 --> 00:04:53,491
<i> GUY HAS MADE A CD COPY FOR ME.</i> 

105
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:56,127
      <i> BILL'S UNCLE HARRY</i>       
       <i> IS SPEAKING NOW.</i>        

106
00:04:56,196 --> 00:04:59,030
 She just shook hands with me   
   as she came off the boat     

107
00:04:59,099 --> 00:05:00,398
      and recognized me.        

108
00:05:00,467 --> 00:05:01,900
         Female Voice:          
        I noticed that.         

109
00:05:01,969 --> 00:05:05,470
    <i> IVA TOGURI, THE WOMAN</i>      
 <i> WHO WAS TRIED AS TOKYO ROSE,</i>  

110
00:05:05,539 --> 00:05:07,205
   <i> WAS BORN IN LOS ANGELES</i>     

111
00:05:07,274 --> 00:05:09,908
     <i> TO FIRST-GENERATION</i>       
     <i> JAPANESE IMMIGRANTS.</i>      

112
00:05:09,977 --> 00:05:12,177
      <i> SHE LEFT THE U.S.</i>        
     <i> IN THE SUMMER OF '41</i>      

113
00:05:12,246 --> 00:05:14,512
   <i> TO CARE FOR A SICK AUNT</i>     
          <i> IN TOKYO.</i>            

114
00:05:14,581 --> 00:05:17,482
     <i> AFTER PEARL HARBOR,</i>       
     <i> WARTIME BUREAUCRACY</i>       

115
00:05:17,551 --> 00:05:21,753
  <i> MADE IT IMPOSSIBLE FOR HER</i>   
    <i> TO RETURN TO THE U.S.</i>      

116
00:05:21,822 --> 00:05:24,222
      <i> STRANDED IN JAPAN</i>        
       <i> DURING THE WAR,</i>         

117
00:05:24,291 --> 00:05:26,791
       <i> IVA FOUND A JOB</i>         
  <i> AT RADIO TOKYO AS A TYPIST</i>   

118
00:05:26,860 --> 00:05:28,827
     <i> UNTIL SHE WAS TAPPED</i>      
           <i> TO HOST</i>             

119
00:05:28,895 --> 00:05:31,630
        <i> A JAPANESE WAR</i>         
     <i> PROPAGANDA PROGRAM.</i>       

120
00:05:31,698 --> 00:05:35,000
  <i> IVA'S BROADCASTS WOULD BE</i>    
<i> AT THE CENTER OF WHAT WAS THEN</i> 

121
00:05:35,068 --> 00:05:38,136
 <i> ONE OF THE COSTLIEST TRIALS</i>   
       <i> IN U.S. HISTORY.</i>        

122
00:05:38,205 --> 00:05:43,608
        THAT TRIAL COST         
 THE U.S. GOVERNMENT $750,000.  

123
00:05:43,677 --> 00:05:46,611
       IN TODAY'S MONEY         
   THAT'S ALMOST $7 MILLION.    

124
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:49,014
     <i> OF THE EIGHT COUNTS</i>       
     <i> BROUGHT AGAINST HER,</i>      

125
00:05:49,082 --> 00:05:52,117
<i> THE GRAND JURY FOUND HER GUILTY</i>
         <i> OF ONLY ONE,</i>          

126
00:05:52,185 --> 00:05:56,755
     <i> ANNOUNCING THE LOSS</i>       
      <i> OF AMERICAN SHIPS.</i>       

127
00:05:56,823 --> 00:05:58,757
    <i> I'M IN NEW YORK CITY,</i>      

128
00:05:58,825 --> 00:06:01,259
 <i> MEETING WITH MEDIA HISTORIAN</i>  
        <i> STEVEN PHIPPS.</i>         

129
00:06:01,328 --> 00:06:03,561
               I'M EAGER FOR YOU
               TO HEAR THIS.    

130
00:06:03,630 --> 00:06:05,330
         Female Voice:          
     There are crowds here      

131
00:06:05,399 --> 00:06:07,632
    that have been standing     
    since 9:00 this morning     

132
00:06:07,701 --> 00:06:09,834
  waiting to see Tokyo Rose,    

133
00:06:09,903 --> 00:06:12,537
    the girl who undermined     
 the morale -- or tried to --   

134
00:06:12,606 --> 00:06:14,706
          of our boys           
        in the Pacific.         

135
00:06:14,775 --> 00:06:17,008
WELL, THIS IS OBVIOUSLY         
A NEWS REPORT,                  

136
00:06:17,077 --> 00:06:21,780
AND IT'S CLEAR THAT IT MUST     
HAVE BEEN SEPTEMBER 25, 1948.   

137
00:06:21,848 --> 00:06:24,649
 <i> STEVEN SAYS THAT'S WHEN IVA</i>   
<i> RETURNED TO THE UNITED STATES</i>  

138
00:06:24,718 --> 00:06:26,551
     <i> BY MILITARY ESCORT.</i>       

139
00:06:26,620 --> 00:06:29,287
<i> THE PRESS AND PUBLIC CLAMORED</i>  
      <i> FOR A CLOSER LOOK</i>        

140
00:06:29,356 --> 00:06:31,623
    <i> AT THE WOMAN THE MEDIA</i>     
     <i> HAD ALREADY BRANDED</i>       

141
00:06:31,692 --> 00:06:34,492
      <i> A WARTIME TRAITOR:</i>       
         <i> TOKYO ROSE.</i>           

142
00:06:34,561 --> 00:06:37,962
BUT THERE WAS NO EVIDENCE       
THAT SHE WAS<i> THE</i> TOKYO ROSE.    

143
00:06:38,031 --> 00:06:42,067
IN FACT, THERE WAS NO ONE PERSON
WHO WAS<i> THE</i> TOKYO ROSE.         

144
00:06:42,135 --> 00:06:45,070
   <i> AS BILL TOLD ME EARLIER,</i>    
   <i> THE G.I.s USED THAT NAME</i>    

145
00:06:45,138 --> 00:06:47,238
 <i> FOR ALL THE ENGLISH-SPEAKING</i>  
         <i> FEMALE HOSTS</i>          

146
00:06:47,340 --> 00:06:49,240
 <i> BROADCASTING IN THE PACIFIC.</i>  

147
00:06:49,309 --> 00:06:51,943
THE JAPANESE FELT THAT          
USING A WOMAN ANNOUNCER         

148
00:06:52,012 --> 00:06:55,013
WOULD MAKE THE G.I.s            
MORE PRONE TO LISTEN            

149
00:06:55,082 --> 00:06:57,916
AND THAT IT WOULD TEND          
TO MAKE THEM HOMESICK.          

150
00:06:57,984 --> 00:07:00,919
   <i> WHY DID BRUNDIDGE CLAIM</i>     
     <i> IVA WAS TOKYO ROSE?</i>       

151
00:07:00,987 --> 00:07:04,289
 <i> STEVEN HAS DONE SOME DIGGING</i>  
<i> ON THE REPORTER'S BACKGROUND.</i>  

152
00:07:04,357 --> 00:07:06,691
I FOUND QUITE A FEW ARTICLES    
ON BRUNDIDGE,                   

153
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:08,726
SINCE I KNOW THAT               
YOU'RE INTERESTED IN HIM.       

154
00:07:08,795 --> 00:07:11,096
   <i> MUCH OF HIS EARLY CAREER</i>    
      <i> WAS IN ST. LOUIS,</i>        

155
00:07:11,164 --> 00:07:12,831
    <i> REPORTING ON THE MOB.</i>      

156
00:07:12,899 --> 00:07:15,767
 <i> STEVEN DISCOVERED BRUNDIDGE</i>   
 <i> HAD A FLAIR FOR THE DRAMATIC</i>  

157
00:07:15,836 --> 00:07:18,336
<i> AND OFTEN PLAYED FAST AND LOOSE</i>
       <i> WITH THE FACTS.</i>         

158
00:07:18,405 --> 00:07:20,305
HERE'S ONE FROM 1930.           

159
00:07:20,373 --> 00:07:23,641
THIS ONE IS CALLED              
"CALL BRUNDIDGE STORY HEARSAY." 

160
00:07:23,710 --> 00:07:26,010
           SO FOR YEARS HE'D    
           BEEN KNOWN AS SOMEONE

161
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:27,712
       WHO WAS PUSHING          
       THE TRUTH ON HIS STORIES.

162
00:07:27,781 --> 00:07:29,180
    WELL, YES.                  

163
00:07:29,249 --> 00:07:31,516
   <i> WHAT WAS HIS INVOLVEMENT</i>    
   <i> IN THE TOKYO ROSE STORY?</i>    

164
00:07:31,585 --> 00:07:33,551
LET ME SHOW YOU                 
IN THIS ARTICLE.                

165
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:36,554
       <i> IT'S A MAY 1948</i>         
       <i> FRONT-PAGE STORY</i>        

166
00:07:36,623 --> 00:07:38,656
<i> FROM</i> THE NASHVILLE TENNESSEAN. 

167
00:07:38,725 --> 00:07:41,593
  <i> THAT'S FOUR MONTHS BEFORE</i>    
  <i> THE DATE ON OUR RECORDING.</i>   

168
00:07:41,661 --> 00:07:44,395
   <i> IN IT, BRUNDIDGE DETAILS</i>    
      <i> HIS TIME IN JAPAN</i>        

169
00:07:44,464 --> 00:07:48,533
<i> HUNTING FOR EMPEROR HIROHITO,</i>  
     <i> THEN FOR TOKYO ROSE.</i>      

170
00:07:48,602 --> 00:07:52,470
<i> IN HIS STORY, BRUNDIDGE TAKES</i>  
  <i> CREDIT FOR HER INDICTMENT.</i>   

171
00:07:52,539 --> 00:07:55,240
THERE'S A REFERENCE             
TO SECRET WITNESSES             

172
00:07:55,308 --> 00:07:57,008
THAT BRUNDIDGE CAME UP WITH.    

173
00:07:57,077 --> 00:07:58,510
                  BUT DO WE KNOW
                  WHO THEY WERE?

174
00:07:58,578 --> 00:08:00,011
I HAVE NO CLUE.                 

175
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:02,080
   <i> STEVEN GIVES ME THE NAME</i>    
       <i> OF A JOURNALIST</i>         

176
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:04,983
   <i> WHO REVISITED THIS STORY</i>    
        <i> IN THE 1970s.</i>          

177
00:08:05,051 --> 00:08:07,418
          <i> RON YATES,</i>           
 <i> ONCE THE TOKYO BUREAU CHIEF</i>   

178
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:09,020
   <i> OF THE</i> CHICAGO TRIBUNE,     

179
00:08:09,089 --> 00:08:11,289
  <i> WROTE A SERIES OF ARTICLES</i>   
           <i> IN 1976</i>             

180
00:08:11,358 --> 00:08:13,224
   <i> ON THE TOKYO ROSE TRIAL.</i>    

181
00:08:13,293 --> 00:08:14,726
     <i> WE'VE AGREED TO MEET</i>      

182
00:08:14,794 --> 00:08:18,830
   <i> AT THE JAPANESE AMERICAN</i>    
<i> NATIONAL MUSEUM IN LOS ANGELES.</i>

183
00:08:18,899 --> 00:08:20,765
   WELL, HERE'S THE RECORD      
   I WAS TELLING YOU ABOUT, RON.

184
00:08:20,834 --> 00:08:22,433
OH, WOW, LOOK AT THAT.          

185
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:25,136
         I'M INVESTIGATING A MAN
         NAMED HARRY BRUNDIDGE. 

186
00:08:25,205 --> 00:08:26,971
              THEY MENTION HIM  
              ON THIS RECORDING.

187
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:28,406
         DO YOU KNOW WHO HE WAS?

188
00:08:28,475 --> 00:08:31,075
OH, YEAH, HARRY BRUNDIDGE IS    
A VERY INTERESTING CHARACTER.   

189
00:08:31,144 --> 00:08:33,077
         <i> RON EXPLAINS</i>          
     <i> HOW HARRY BRUNDIDGE</i>       

190
00:08:33,146 --> 00:08:35,179
  <i> HAD FIRST BECOME INVOLVED</i>    
       <i> WITH TOKYO ROSE</i>         

191
00:08:35,248 --> 00:08:36,948
 <i> THREE YEARS BEFORE THE TRIAL</i>  

192
00:08:37,017 --> 00:08:39,550
  <i> IN THE IMMEDIATE AFTERMATH</i>   
       <i> OF WORLD WAR II.</i>        

193
00:08:39,619 --> 00:08:41,419
    <i> THAT'S WHEN BRUNDIDGE</i>      
        <i> HOOKED UP WITH</i>         

194
00:08:41,488 --> 00:08:43,588
  <i> VETERAN WAR CORRESPONDENT</i>    
          <i> CLARK LEE.</i>           

195
00:08:43,657 --> 00:08:45,924
     <i> THEY HEADED TO JAPAN</i>      
           <i> IN 1945</i>             

196
00:08:45,992 --> 00:08:48,927
   <i> IN PURSUIT OF THE SCOOP</i>     
        <i> OF A LIFETIME.</i>         

197
00:08:48,995 --> 00:08:52,664
THEY THOUGHT, "WE'LL FIND TOKYO 
ROSE AND THAT'LL BE OUR STORY." 

198
00:08:52,732 --> 00:08:55,333
THEY SAID, "WE WILL PAY HER     
$2,000 IF SHE'LL COME           

199
00:08:55,402 --> 00:08:57,735
TO THE IMPERIAL HOTEL           
TO BE INTERVIEWED."             

200
00:08:57,804 --> 00:09:00,838
   <i> IN WAR-TORN TOKYO, WHERE</i>    
  <i> MOST PEOPLE WERE STARVING,</i>   

201
00:09:00,907 --> 00:09:04,008
<i> THAT MONEY MIGHT GET HER HOME</i>  
    <i> TO THE UNITED STATES.</i>      

202
00:09:04,077 --> 00:09:05,843
BUT WHEN SHE WALKED             
INTO THE ROOM,                  

203
00:09:05,912 --> 00:09:07,712
THIS WAS NOT                    
WHAT THEY WERE EXPECTING.       

204
00:09:07,781 --> 00:09:10,014
       <i> IN HER PIGTAILS</i>         
      <i> AND SADDLE SHOES,</i>        

205
00:09:10,083 --> 00:09:12,583
      <i> IVA NEITHER LOOKED</i>       
     <i> NOR SOUNDED THE PART</i>      

206
00:09:12,652 --> 00:09:14,585
 <i> OF THE MATAHARI OF THE EAST.</i>  

207
00:09:14,654 --> 00:09:18,156
  <i> RON SHOWS ME A REENACTMENT</i>   
   <i> OF A</i> ZERO HOUR<i> BROADCAST</i>    

208
00:09:18,224 --> 00:09:21,426
 <i> THAT IVA LATER AGREED TO DO</i>   
 <i> FOR THE U.S. ARMY IN TOKYO.</i>   

209
00:09:21,494 --> 00:09:22,960
     Greetings, everybody.      

210
00:09:23,029 --> 00:09:25,496
This is your number-one enemy,  
    your favorite playmate,     

211
00:09:25,565 --> 00:09:27,465
    Orphan Ann, ready again     

212
00:09:27,534 --> 00:09:29,901
     for a vicious assault      
        on your morale.         

213
00:09:29,969 --> 00:09:31,936
      <i> RON EXPLAINS THAT</i>        
       <i> ALL THE SCRIPTS</i>         

214
00:09:32,005 --> 00:09:34,105
         <i> WERE WRITTEN</i>          
      <i> BY ALLIED P.O.W.s,</i>       

215
00:09:34,174 --> 00:09:37,108
   <i> WHO ALSO HAD BEEN FORCED</i>    
   <i> TO WORK FOR RADIO TOKYO.</i>    

216
00:09:37,177 --> 00:09:39,944
  <i> THE LANGUAGE WAS INTENDED</i>    
    <i> TO BE TONGUE-IN-CHEEK,</i>     

217
00:09:40,013 --> 00:09:41,979
     <i> THE KIND OF TEASING</i>       
        <i> THAT AMERICANS</i>         

218
00:09:42,048 --> 00:09:43,748
   <i> WOULD EASILY RECOGNIZE.</i>     

219
00:09:43,817 --> 00:09:45,483
AND THEY'D ALWAYS GO OVER       
THE SCRIPTS WITH HER AND SAY,   

220
00:09:45,552 --> 00:09:47,085
"HERE'S WHAT WE WANT YOU        
TO SAY, IVA."                   

221
00:09:47,153 --> 00:09:48,853
AND THEN SHE WOULD SAY          
THESE THINGS,                   

222
00:09:48,922 --> 00:09:51,589
LIKE "HELLO, MY HONORABLE       
BONEHEADS OF THE PACIFIC.       

223
00:09:51,658 --> 00:09:53,591
"THIS IS YOUR FAVORITE ENEMY,   
ORPHAN ANN.                     

224
00:09:53,660 --> 00:09:55,593
I'M GOING TO SNEAK UP BEHIND YOU
WITH MY NAIL FILE."             

225
00:09:55,662 --> 00:09:58,863
YOU SEE IN HER FACE THAT        
SHE KNOWS SHE'S SAYING THINGS   

226
00:09:58,932 --> 00:10:01,065
THAT WOULD SOUND MEAN           
TO THE JAPANESE                 

227
00:10:01,134 --> 00:10:04,102
BUT THAT IT'S ACTUALLY AN INSIDE
JOKE AMONG ALL THE AMERICANS.   

228
00:10:04,170 --> 00:10:06,170
           RIGHT, THERE'S A REAL
           FACETIOUSNESS TO IT. 

229
00:10:06,239 --> 00:10:09,340
    <i> WHEN BRUNDIDGE AND LEE</i>     
   <i> INTERVIEWED IVA IN 1945,</i>    

230
00:10:09,409 --> 00:10:12,810
<i> THAT TEASING TONE NEVER MADE IT</i>
      <i> INTO THEIR NOTES.</i>        

231
00:10:12,879 --> 00:10:14,645
    <i> THEY HAD OTHER PLANS.</i>      

232
00:10:14,714 --> 00:10:16,347
THE STORY JUST WASN'T THERE.    

233
00:10:16,416 --> 00:10:18,750
THIS WAS NOT THE SIREN          
OF THE PACIFIC.                 

234
00:10:18,818 --> 00:10:22,320
<i> BRUNDIDGE TOOK OUT THE CONTRACT</i>
         <i> FOR $2,000,</i>           

235
00:10:22,388 --> 00:10:25,123
        <i> THEN ASKED IVA</i>         
     <i> A FATEFUL QUESTION.</i>       

236
00:10:25,191 --> 00:10:26,991
"JUST FOR THE HECK OF IT,       
WOULD YOU JUST SIGN THIS        

237
00:10:27,060 --> 00:10:28,860
AS TOKYO ROSE?"                 

238
00:10:28,928 --> 00:10:32,029
AND SHE SAID, "SURE."           

239
00:10:32,098 --> 00:10:35,299
WHAT HE DID WAS                 
HE TOOK THOSE NOTES             

240
00:10:35,368 --> 00:10:38,636
AND GAVE THEM TO THE            
OCCUPATION FORCES, AUTHORITIES, 

241
00:10:38,705 --> 00:10:43,474
AND SAID, "I HAVE THE SIGNED    
CONFESSION OF TOKYO ROSE HERE." 

242
00:10:43,543 --> 00:10:46,911
AND WITHIN A FEW DAYS           
SHE WAS ARRESTED.               

243
00:10:46,980 --> 00:10:49,914
   <i> SHE WAS FIRST IMPRISONED</i>    
  <i> IN TOKYO UNDER MARTIAL LAW</i>   

244
00:10:49,983 --> 00:10:52,116
     <i> AND HELD FOR A YEAR</i>       
        <i> WHILE THE ARMY</i>         

245
00:10:52,185 --> 00:10:54,619
  <i> COUNTER INTELLIGENCE CORPS</i>   
        <i> INVESTIGATED.</i>          

246
00:10:54,687 --> 00:10:56,787
     <i> FINDING NO EVIDENCE</i>       
         <i> OF TREASON,</i>           

247
00:10:56,856 --> 00:10:59,557
  <i> THE WAR DEPARTMENT CLEARED</i>   
  <i> AND FINALLY RELEASED HER.</i>    

248
00:10:59,626 --> 00:11:01,659
    <i> THAT SHOULD HAVE BEEN</i>      
        <i> THE END OF IT.</i>         

249
00:11:01,728 --> 00:11:05,663
 SO BRUNDIDGE MET HER IN '45,   
 '46 SHE'S RELEASED FROM PRISON,

250
00:11:05,732 --> 00:11:08,199
       HOW DID IT BECOME A STORY
       AGAIN IN 1948?           

251
00:11:08,268 --> 00:11:10,034
THAT IS A STORY IN ITSELF.      

252
00:11:10,103 --> 00:11:12,036
      <i> AFTER BEING FREED</i>        
      <i> BY THE U.S. ARMY,</i>        

253
00:11:12,105 --> 00:11:14,572
       <i> IVA HAD APPLIED</i>         
      <i> FOR REPATRIATION.</i>        

254
00:11:14,641 --> 00:11:17,441
  <i> BUT THE POPULAR RADIO HOST</i>   
       <i> WALTER WINCHELL</i>         

255
00:11:17,510 --> 00:11:20,244
    <i> LEARNED OF THE REQUEST</i>     
    <i> AND STARTED A CAMPAIGN</i>     

256
00:11:20,313 --> 00:11:23,814
    <i> TO PREVENT HER RETURN</i>      
   <i> AND TRY HER FOR TREASON.</i>    

257
00:11:23,883 --> 00:11:25,349
GOLD STAR MOTHERS --            
THESE ARE MOTHERS               

258
00:11:25,418 --> 00:11:27,919
WHO HAD LOST THEIR SONS         
FIGHTING IN THE PACIFIC --      

259
00:11:27,987 --> 00:11:29,754
BEGAN WRITING                   
TO WALTER WINCHELL,             

260
00:11:29,822 --> 00:11:31,756
HE FORWARDED THOSE              
TO THE TRUMAN ADMINISTRATION,   

261
00:11:31,824 --> 00:11:33,257
AND THAT PRESSURE BEGAN         
TO BUILD.                       

262
00:11:33,326 --> 00:11:34,792
   <i> IT WAS AN ELECTION YEAR.</i>    

263
00:11:34,861 --> 00:11:37,862
<i> RON SAYS CHARGES OF BEING SOFT</i> 
  <i> ON COMMUNISTS AND TRAITORS</i>   

264
00:11:37,931 --> 00:11:39,630
    <i> WAS A CRITICAL FACTOR</i>      

265
00:11:39,699 --> 00:11:42,600
<i> IN TRUMAN'S CLOSE PRESIDENTIAL</i> 
  <i> RACE AGAINST THOMAS DEWEY.</i>   

266
00:11:42,669 --> 00:11:44,635
THE TRUMAN ADMINISTRATION       
DOESN'T WANT TO BE PERCEIVED    

267
00:11:44,704 --> 00:11:46,370
AS BEING SOFT ON TRAITORS.      

268
00:11:46,439 --> 00:11:49,440
  <i> THE DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE</i>    
<i> ISSUED A REQUEST FOR WITNESSES</i> 

269
00:11:49,509 --> 00:11:52,376
    <i> TO IVA'S ALLEGED ACTS</i>      
         <i> OF TREASON.</i>           

270
00:11:52,445 --> 00:11:54,612
SO HERE COMES BRUNDIDGE AGAIN.  

271
00:11:54,681 --> 00:11:57,415
  <i> WHEN BRUNDIDGE MET UP WITH</i>   
 <i> ATTORNEY GENERAL TOM CLARK,</i>   

272
00:11:57,483 --> 00:11:59,951
      <i> HE OFFERED TO GET</i>        
  <i> A NEW CONFESSION FROM IVA</i>    

273
00:12:00,019 --> 00:12:02,853
    <i> AND TO FIND WITNESSES</i>      
     <i> TO HELP CONVICT HER.</i>      

274
00:12:02,922 --> 00:12:05,656
TOM CLARK ASSIGNS SOME OF       
HIS MINIONS TO GO BACK TO TOKYO,

275
00:12:05,725 --> 00:12:07,625
AND HARRY BRUNDIDGE             
GOES WITH THEM.                 

276
00:12:07,694 --> 00:12:09,360
   <i> RON SAYS IT WASN'T UNTIL</i>    

277
00:12:09,429 --> 00:12:11,629
      <i> A QUARTER-CENTURY</i>        
      <i> AFTER IVA'S TRIAL</i>        

278
00:12:11,698 --> 00:12:13,597
       <i> THAT HE UNLOCKED</i>        
       <i> A CRUCIAL PIECE</i>         

279
00:12:13,666 --> 00:12:15,633
<i> OF THE GOVERNMENT'S STRATEGY.</i>  

280
00:12:15,702 --> 00:12:19,403
 <i> RON ARRANGED TO MEET TWO MEN</i>  
 <i> WHO HAD HELD ON TO A SECRET:</i>  

281
00:12:19,472 --> 00:12:22,239
       <i> GEORGE MITSUSHIO</i>        
         <i> AND KEN OKI,</i>          

282
00:12:22,308 --> 00:12:25,042
       <i> IVA'S OLD BOSSES</i>        
      <i> FROM RADIO TOKYO.</i>        

283
00:12:25,111 --> 00:12:28,813
THEY SAID, "WE -- OUR TESTIMONY 
IS WHAT CONVICTED HER,          

284
00:12:28,881 --> 00:12:30,548
AND IT WAS ALL A LIE."          

285
00:12:30,616 --> 00:12:32,416
THEY HAD BEEN COACHED           
FOR TWO MONTHS                  

286
00:12:32,485 --> 00:12:33,818
BY THE JUSTICE DEPARTMENT       

287
00:12:33,886 --> 00:12:35,553
IN WHAT THEY SHOULD SAY         
AT THE TRIAL.                   

288
00:12:35,621 --> 00:12:39,890
AND THEIR TESTIMONY WAS         
THE SIXTH OF THE EIGHT COUNTS   

289
00:12:39,959 --> 00:12:41,359
WHICH SHE WAS INDICTED ON,      

290
00:12:41,427 --> 00:12:43,060
THAT SHE DID SPEAK              
INTO A MICROPHONE               

291
00:12:43,129 --> 00:12:44,295
ABOUT THE LOSS OF SHIPS.        

292
00:12:44,364 --> 00:12:45,830
        <i> BUT WHAT ABOUT</i>         
      <i> BRUNDIDGE'S CLAIMS</i>       

293
00:12:45,898 --> 00:12:48,199
    <i> OF FINDING ADDITIONAL</i>      
      <i> SECRET WITNESSES?</i>        

294
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:50,835
I KNOW THE PERFECT PERSON       
TO TELL YOU ABOUT THEM.         

295
00:12:50,903 --> 00:12:53,971
   <i> I'M MEETING WITH BARBARA</i>    
<i> TREMBLEY AT DARKWOOD STUDIOS.</i>  

296
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:56,474
       <i> BARBARA MET IVA</i>         
        <i> 20 YEARS AGO.</i>          

297
00:12:56,542 --> 00:12:58,943
<i> OVER TIME THEY BECAME FRIENDS.</i> 

298
00:12:59,011 --> 00:13:01,379
      <i> IVA AGREED TO TELL</i>       
        <i> HER FULL STORY</i>         

299
00:13:01,447 --> 00:13:03,114
 <i> AND GAVE BARBARA THE RIGHTS</i>   

300
00:13:03,182 --> 00:13:05,383
       <i> TO MAKE HER SAGA</i>        
     <i> INTO A FEATURE FILM.</i>      

301
00:13:05,451 --> 00:13:08,018
I HAVE A RECORDING              
THAT IS DESCRIBING THE MOMENT   

302
00:13:08,087 --> 00:13:09,954
WHEN IVA COMES BACK             
TO THE UNITED STATES.           

303
00:13:10,022 --> 00:13:11,922
     <i> I TELL BARBARA THAT</i>       
      <i> ON THIS RECORDING</i>        

304
00:13:11,991 --> 00:13:15,126
<i> BRUNDIDGE BOASTS OF GETTING IVA</i>
  <i> TO SIGN A NEW CONFESSION.</i>    

305
00:13:15,194 --> 00:13:17,361
WHY IS IVA EVEN WILLING         
TO SEE HIM,                     

306
00:13:17,430 --> 00:13:19,230
MUCH LESS TO SIGN               
THIS DOCUMENT?                  

307
00:13:19,298 --> 00:13:21,098
     SHE HAD JUST LOST HER BABY.

308
00:13:21,167 --> 00:13:24,268
  <i> BARBARA EXPLAINS THAT IVA</i>    
<i> HAD JUST SUFFERED A MISCARRIAGE</i>

309
00:13:24,337 --> 00:13:26,871
    <i> AND DESPERATELY WANTED</i>     
  <i> TO GET HOME TO THE STATES.</i>   

310
00:13:26,939 --> 00:13:30,241
    <i> IVA TOLD BARBARA THAT</i>      
  <i> BRUNDIDGE HAD ASSURED HER</i>    

311
00:13:30,309 --> 00:13:33,477
  <i> THAT SIGNING THE DOCUMENT</i>    
     <i> WAS A PASSPORT HOME.</i>      

312
00:13:33,546 --> 00:13:35,079
               AND THEN AS SOON 
               AS SHE SIGNED IT,

313
00:13:35,148 --> 00:13:36,914
    BRUNDIDGE LEANED OVER TO IVA
    AND HE SAID,                

314
00:13:36,983 --> 00:13:38,549
           "YOU'VE DONE YOURSELF
           A GOOD DEAL.         

315
00:13:38,618 --> 00:13:40,351
           THEY'LL NEVER EXECUTE
           A WOMAN."            

316
00:13:40,420 --> 00:13:43,821
              SHE LOST HER HEART
              AT THAT POINT.    

317
00:13:43,890 --> 00:13:46,824
BRUNDIDGE HAD WRITTEN           
ABOUT SECRET WITNESSES          

318
00:13:46,893 --> 00:13:48,826
THAT WOULD PROVE THE CASE       
AGAINST IVA.                    

319
00:13:48,895 --> 00:13:50,494
                  YES, MR. YAGI.

320
00:13:50,563 --> 00:13:52,429
       YAGI WAS ACTUALLY SOMEONE
       THAT BRUNDIDGE HAD KNOWN 

321
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:53,931
                 BEFORE THE WAR.

322
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,500
    <i> BARBARA SAYS THAT WHEN</i>     
 <i> BRUNDIDGE TRAVELED TO JAPAN,</i>  

323
00:13:56,569 --> 00:13:58,702
 <i> HIROM YAGI ACTED AS A FIXER,</i>  

324
00:13:58,771 --> 00:14:01,071
  <i> MAKING LOCAL INTRODUCTIONS</i>   
     <i> FOR THE JOURNALIST.</i>       

325
00:14:01,140 --> 00:14:02,873
 BRUNDIDGE LITERALLY BRIBED HIM.

326
00:14:02,942 --> 00:14:04,708
          HE SAID, "YOU WILL GET
          A TRIP TO THE U.S.    

327
00:14:04,777 --> 00:14:06,377
               "AND WE'LL HAVE  
               A WONDERFUL TIME.

328
00:14:06,445 --> 00:14:08,312
  "ALL YOU HAVE TO DO IS TESTIFY
  FOR THE GRAND JURY,           

329
00:14:08,381 --> 00:14:09,980
               AND THIS IS ALL  
               YOU HAVE TO SAY."

330
00:14:10,049 --> 00:14:12,283
        <i> BARBARA FOUND</i>          
  <i> THE HANDWRITTEN TESTIMONY</i>    

331
00:14:12,351 --> 00:14:16,086
   <i> YAGI HAD GIVEN BRUNDIDGE</i>    
<i> AND THE U.S. ATTORNEY GENERAL.</i> 

332
00:14:16,155 --> 00:14:17,955
            "I HEARD HER SAY    
            INTO THE MICROPHONE,

333
00:14:18,024 --> 00:14:20,224
             'YOUR WIVES ARE OUT
             WITH WAR WORKERS.'"

334
00:14:20,293 --> 00:14:22,226
SO DOES HE TESTIFY              
AT THE TRIAL                    

335
00:14:22,295 --> 00:14:23,327
BEFORE THE GRAND JURY?          

336
00:14:23,396 --> 00:14:24,628
                   YES, HE DOES.

337
00:14:24,697 --> 00:14:26,931
     BUT AS SOON AS HE GETS BACK
     TO JAPAN, HE RECANTS.      

338
00:14:26,999 --> 00:14:28,966
       YAGI EVEN WRITES A LETTER
       TO BRUNDIDGE             

339
00:14:29,035 --> 00:14:31,635
  ASKING HIM TO PLEASE STOP THIS
  BEFORE IT'S TOO LATE.         

340
00:14:31,704 --> 00:14:34,538
    "DEAR MR. BRUNDIDGE, THIS IS
    AN ELEVENTH HOUR APPEAL     

341
00:14:34,607 --> 00:14:36,607
            "ASKING YOU TO USE  
            YOUR GOOD INFLUENCES

342
00:14:36,676 --> 00:14:39,043
   TO CALL OFF THE COMING TRIAL,
   IF POSSIBLE."                

343
00:14:39,111 --> 00:14:41,111
 <i> BARBARA EXPLAINS THAT BY NOW</i>  
        <i> THE GOVERNMENT</i>         

344
00:14:41,180 --> 00:14:43,147
      <i> HAD SERIOUS DOUBTS</i>       
       <i> ABOUT BRUNDIDGE</i>         

345
00:14:43,216 --> 00:14:46,483
<i> AND EVEN BEGAN TO INVESTIGATE</i>  
  <i> HIM FOR WITNESS TAMPERING,</i>   

346
00:14:46,552 --> 00:14:50,120
<i> BUT THEY HAD TOO MUCH INVESTED</i> 
<i> IN THE TRIAL TO BACK OUT NOW.</i>  

347
00:14:50,189 --> 00:14:52,990
      THE DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE,
      TOM CLARK, AND SO ON,     

348
00:14:53,059 --> 00:14:55,759
       THEY PUT A LID ON IT     
       AND IT BECAME A COVER-UP.

349
00:14:55,828 --> 00:14:57,861
     <i> THE TRIAL PROCEEDED</i>       
         <i> AS PLANNED,</i>           

350
00:14:57,930 --> 00:14:59,997
       <i> BUT DID IT GO ON</i>        
       <i> WITH BRUNDIDGE?</i>         

351
00:15:00,066 --> 00:15:02,233
          THAT'S WHEN IT BECOMES
          VERY INTERESTING.     

352
00:15:02,301 --> 00:15:05,736
    <i> THE CONFIDENTIAL FILES</i>     
<i> OF FBI DIRECTOR J. EDGAR HOOVER</i>

353
00:15:05,805 --> 00:15:08,005
     <i> WERE OPENED IN 2005.</i>      

354
00:15:08,074 --> 00:15:10,207
      <i> IN THOSE DOCUMENTS</i>       
      <i> BARBARA HAS FOUND</i>        

355
00:15:10,276 --> 00:15:11,875
    <i> SOME ANSWERS FOR BILL.</i>     

356
00:15:11,944 --> 00:15:14,044
LET ME PLAY FOR YOU             
WHAT'S ON YOUR RECORD,          

357
00:15:14,113 --> 00:15:17,114
AND THEN WE HEAR A VOICE        
YOU MAY RECOGNIZE.              

358
00:15:17,183 --> 00:15:20,284
    Brundidge on recording:     
  I went back at the request    
    of the attorney general     

359
00:15:20,353 --> 00:15:23,787
          last March,           
 and Rose willingly signed it.  

360
00:15:23,856 --> 00:15:25,789
          I RECOGNIZE HIS VOICE.

361
00:15:25,858 --> 00:15:27,658
        THAT WAS MY UNCLE HARRY.

362
00:15:27,727 --> 00:15:29,693
         <i> I TELL BILL</i>           
    <i> ABOUT HIS UNCLE'S ROLE</i>     

363
00:15:29,762 --> 00:15:31,862
          <i> IN LINKING</i>           
   <i> THE REAL-LIFE IVA TOGURI</i>    

364
00:15:31,931 --> 00:15:34,298
  <i> AND THE FABLED TOKYO ROSE.</i>   

365
00:15:34,367 --> 00:15:36,066
           THAT'S SAD, ISN'T IT?

366
00:15:36,135 --> 00:15:37,534
    YEAH.                       

367
00:15:37,603 --> 00:15:40,738
   HE PROBABLY DID MOST ANYTHING
   TO GET A STORY,              

368
00:15:40,806 --> 00:15:42,640
       AND THAT WAS A BIG STORY.

369
00:15:42,708 --> 00:15:44,475
YOU'D WANTED TO KNOW            
WHAT PART                       

370
00:15:44,543 --> 00:15:46,276
HARRY BRUNDIDGE PLAYED          
IN THIS TRIAL.                  

371
00:15:46,345 --> 00:15:48,512
WHEN HE MENTIONED THAT          
THE ATTORNEY GENERAL'S OFFICE   

372
00:15:48,581 --> 00:15:50,014
HAD SENT HIM BACK,              

373
00:15:50,082 --> 00:15:53,951
THAT'S WHERE THE STORY BECOMES  
LARGER THAN JUST YOUR UNCLE.    

374
00:15:54,020 --> 00:15:56,387
SO WHAT WAS BRUNDIDGE'S ROLE    
IN THE TRIAL?                   

375
00:15:56,455 --> 00:15:58,655
     WELL, BRUNDIDGE HAD NO ROLE
     IN THE TRIAL.              

376
00:15:58,724 --> 00:16:00,791
           THEY DIDN'T ALLOW HIM
           TO TESTIFY.          

377
00:16:00,860 --> 00:16:03,827
      THE FBI,                  
      THE DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE:

378
00:16:03,896 --> 00:16:06,864
  HE WAS SUCH A HOT POTATO,     
  NOBODY WANTED TO GET NEAR HIM.

379
00:16:06,932 --> 00:16:08,999
    <i> ON ONE INTERNAL MEMO,</i>      
      <i> BARBARA DISCOVERED</i>       

380
00:16:09,068 --> 00:16:11,168
     <i> THAT J. EDGAR HOOVER</i>      
        <i> HAD WEIGHED IN</i>         

381
00:16:11,237 --> 00:16:12,836
        <i> ON BRUNDIDGE'S</i>         
      <i> SO-CALLED WITNESS</i>        

382
00:16:12,905 --> 00:16:14,505
   <i> RECANTING HIS TESTIMONY.</i>    

383
00:16:14,573 --> 00:16:16,507
              "I'M NOT SURPRISED
              AT DEVELOPMENTS.  

384
00:16:16,575 --> 00:16:18,709
       "IT WAS MOST UNWISE      
       FOR DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE

385
00:16:18,778 --> 00:16:21,645
  TO USE SUCH A PERSON AS       
  BRUNDIDGE IN THE FIRST PLACE."

386
00:16:21,714 --> 00:16:23,680
    THEY REALIZED THE WHOLE CASE
    COULD BE BLOWN UP           

387
00:16:23,749 --> 00:16:25,182
                IF HE TESTIFIED.

388
00:16:25,251 --> 00:16:28,252
HE FINALLY WENT TO THE DEFENSE  
AND OFFERED TO TESTIFY FOR THEM,

389
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,320
     AND THEY WOULDN'T TOUCH HIM
     EITHER.                    

390
00:16:30,389 --> 00:16:32,156
     GEE, THAT'S SOMETHING ELSE.

391
00:16:32,224 --> 00:16:34,358
    YOU KNOW, BACK IN WAR TIMES,

392
00:16:34,427 --> 00:16:37,161
        PEOPLE LOOKED UPON      
        THE JAPANESE REALLY BAD,

393
00:16:37,229 --> 00:16:39,363
              AND IT DIDN'T MAKE
              ANY DIFFERENCE    

394
00:16:39,432 --> 00:16:41,231
     WHETHER THEY WERE AMERICANS
     OR --                      

395
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:45,202
 LOOK AT ALL THE INTERNEES THEY 
 HAD, AND THEY WERE GOOD PEOPLE.

396
00:16:45,271 --> 00:16:46,637
THEY WERE.                      

397
00:16:46,705 --> 00:16:49,173
BILL, I REALLY WANT TO THANK YOU
FOR GIVING ME THIS RECORD       

398
00:16:49,241 --> 00:16:52,242
AND GIVING ME A CHANCE          
TO SEE THIS LARGER HISTORY.     

399
00:16:52,311 --> 00:16:53,544
THANK YOU.                      

400
00:16:53,612 --> 00:16:54,845
                      THANK<i> YOU.</i>

401
00:16:54,914 --> 00:16:56,914
     I'M GLAD ALL THIS CAME OUT.

402
00:16:56,982 --> 00:17:00,217
I APPRECIATE THE WISDOM         
WITH WHICH YOU HEARD THE STORY. 

403
00:17:00,286 --> 00:17:02,252
     <i> GIVEN THE NEW PUBLIC</i>      
         <i> DISCLOSURES</i>           

404
00:17:02,321 --> 00:17:03,987
    <i> ABOUT IVA'S INNOCENCE</i>      

405
00:17:04,056 --> 00:17:06,423
  <i> AND THE PERJURED TESTIMONY</i>   
         <i> AGAINST HER,</i>          

406
00:17:06,492 --> 00:17:09,626
    <i> PRESIDENT FORD AGREED</i>      
    <i> TO LOOK INTO HER CASE.</i>     

407
00:17:09,695 --> 00:17:12,463
   <i> IN HIS LAST OFFICIAL ACT</i>    
          <i> IN OFFICE,</i>           

408
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:16,667
 <i> HE GRANTED IVA TOGURI A FULL</i>  
   <i> AND UNCONDITIONAL PARDON</i>    

409
00:17:16,735 --> 00:17:20,370
     <i> ON JANUARY 19, 1977.</i>      

410
00:17:20,439 --> 00:17:23,540
       <i> SHE PASSED AWAY</i>         
           <i> IN 2006.</i>            

411
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:28,679
       TWELVE AMERICANS         
    WERE TRIED FOR TREASON      

412
00:17:28,747 --> 00:17:30,347
      AFTER WORLD WAR II.       

413
00:17:30,416 --> 00:17:32,816
SEVEN WERE RADIO BROADCASTERS.  

414
00:17:32,885 --> 00:17:35,686
     AXIS SALLY WAS ONE OF      
      THE MOST INFAMOUS.        

415
00:17:35,754 --> 00:17:39,523
BORN MILDRED GILLARS, SHE DREAMT
    OF BECOMING A STARLET.      

416
00:17:39,592 --> 00:17:42,025
 WITH LITTLE THEATER SUCCESS,   

417
00:17:42,094 --> 00:17:45,762
   GILLARS MOVED TO GERMANY     
       IN THE MID-1930s         

418
00:17:45,831 --> 00:17:48,765
 AND WORKED FOR RADIO BERLIN.   

419
00:17:48,834 --> 00:17:53,036
      FROM DECEMBER 1941        
         TO MAY 1945,           

420
00:17:53,105 --> 00:17:56,073
     GILLARS' SULTRY VOICE      
    REACHED AMERICAN G.I.s      

421
00:17:56,141 --> 00:18:00,510
  WITH PRO-GERMAN WAR UPDATES   
  DESIGNED TO DEPLETE MORALE.   

422
00:18:00,579 --> 00:18:04,448
GILLARS' BROADCASTS CAME UNDER  
THE AUSPICES OF JOSEPH GOEBBELS,

423
00:18:04,516 --> 00:18:06,750
 HITLER'S PROPAGANDA MINISTER.  

424
00:18:06,819 --> 00:18:09,820
   SHE POSED AS AN AMERICAN     
     RED CROSS VOLUNTEER,       

425
00:18:09,888 --> 00:18:14,157
 INTERVIEWING AMERICAN P.O.W.s  
BUT DISTORTING THEIR COMMENTS.  

426
00:18:14,226 --> 00:18:16,860
   SHE CRITICIZED ROOSEVELT     
         AND CHURCHILL          

427
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:19,263
        AND MUSED ABOUT         
      THE UNFAITHFULNESS        

428
00:18:19,331 --> 00:18:22,599
 OF G.I. WIVES AND GIRLFRIENDS  
          BACK HOME.            

429
00:18:22,668 --> 00:18:25,802
         AXIS SALLY'S           
   MOST INFAMOUS BROADCAST,     

430
00:18:25,871 --> 00:18:27,504
     "VISION OF INVASION,"      

431
00:18:27,573 --> 00:18:30,540
   TARGETED AMERICAN TROOPS     
        AWAITING D-DAY.         

432
00:18:30,609 --> 00:18:33,777
 GILLARS PLAYED A G.I. MOTHER   
 DREAMING OF HER SON'S DEATH.   

433
00:18:33,846 --> 00:18:36,313
     CRIES OF THE WOUNDED       
   PLAYED IN THE BACKGROUND,    

434
00:18:36,382 --> 00:18:39,116
    CREATING THE IMPRESSION     
    OF IMPENDING SLAUGHTER.     

435
00:18:39,184 --> 00:18:40,784
    The boys will be killed     

436
00:18:40,853 --> 00:18:42,686
   or crippled for the rest     
        of their lives.         

437
00:18:42,755 --> 00:18:46,123
  AFTER THE WAR, GILLARS WAS    
    EXTRADITED TO THE U.S.      

438
00:18:46,191 --> 00:18:48,625
     SHE WAS FOUND GUILTY       
          OF TREASON            

439
00:18:48,694 --> 00:18:51,862
AND SENTENCED TO 10 TO 30 YEARS 
          IN PRISON.            

440
00:18:51,930 --> 00:18:55,899
  IN 1961, GILLARS LEFT JAIL    
     TO LIVE IN A CONVENT       

441
00:18:55,968 --> 00:18:57,701
  AND TEACH CATHOLIC SCHOOL.    

442
00:18:57,770 --> 00:18:59,736
       SHE DIED IN 1988.        

443
00:19:02,741 --> 00:19:07,344
            Elyse:              
<i> OUR NEXT STORY GOES IN SEARCH</i>  
 <i> OF A NATIVE-AMERICAN LEGEND.</i>  

444
00:19:07,413 --> 00:19:11,648
     <i> MORE THAN 125 YEARS</i>       
       <i> AFTER HIS DEATH,</i>        

445
00:19:11,717 --> 00:19:14,351
     <i> THE NAME CRAZY HORSE</i>      
         <i> STILL ECHOES</i>          

446
00:19:14,420 --> 00:19:16,520
      <i> IN THE BLACK HILLS</i>       
       <i> OF SOUTH DAKOTA.</i>        

447
00:19:16,588 --> 00:19:19,723
 <i> IN LIFE, THE LAKOTA WARRIOR</i>   
      <i> AND SPIRITUAL MAN</i>        

448
00:19:19,792 --> 00:19:22,359
       <i> VOWED TO PROTECT</i>        
 <i> THESE SACRED HUNTING GROUNDS</i>  

449
00:19:22,428 --> 00:19:25,162
  <i> FROM ENCROACHING SETTLERS</i>    
       <i> AND GOLD MINERS.</i>        

450
00:19:25,230 --> 00:19:29,066
   <i> IN 1876, HE HELPED CRUSH</i>    
   <i> THE U.S. CAVALRY TROOPS</i>     

451
00:19:29,134 --> 00:19:32,602
<i> OF GENERAL GEORGE CUSTER AT THE</i>
<i> BATTLE OF THE LITTLE BIGHORN.</i>  

452
00:19:32,671 --> 00:19:35,906
 <i> BUT IS THIS A TRUE LIKENESS</i>   
       <i> OF THE WARRIOR?</i>         

453
00:19:35,974 --> 00:19:39,409
<i> DESPITE HIS FAME, CRAZY HORSE</i>  
 <i> REFUSED TO BE PHOTOGRAPHED,</i>   

454
00:19:39,478 --> 00:19:42,012
       <i> SHUNNING WHITES</i>         
   <i> AND THEIR TECHNOLOGIES.</i>     

455
00:19:42,081 --> 00:19:44,481
      <i> FOR YEARS, RUMORS</i>        
  <i> OF CRAZY HORSE PHOTOGRAPHS</i>   

456
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:47,050
 <i> HAVE TANTALIZED COLLECTORS.</i>   

457
00:19:47,119 --> 00:19:50,821
     <i> MORE THAN 125 YEARS</i>       
  <i> AFTER THE WARRIOR'S DEATH,</i>   

458
00:19:50,889 --> 00:19:53,390
          <i> TIM GIAGO</i>            
 <i> OF RAPID CITY, SOUTH DAKOTA,</i>  

459
00:19:53,459 --> 00:19:55,692
      <i> HAS A FRAMED IMAGE</i>       
         <i> WHICH MAY BE</i>          

460
00:19:55,761 --> 00:19:58,628
 <i> THE ONLY PHOTOGRAPHIC IMAGE</i>   
       <i> OF THIS LEGEND.</i>         

461
00:19:58,697 --> 00:20:01,998
   IT SAID, "TASUNKA WITKO,"    
       AND TASUNKA WITKO        

462
00:20:02,067 --> 00:20:04,835
      IS THE LAKOTA NAME        
    THAT MEANS CRAZY HORSE.     

463
00:20:04,903 --> 00:20:07,904
 <i> I'M MEETING TIM AT HIS HOME</i>   
      <i> TO FIND OUT MORE.</i>        

464
00:20:10,008 --> 00:20:11,808
HI.                             
            WELCOME TO MY HOUSE.

465
00:20:11,877 --> 00:20:13,110
THANK YOU.                      

466
00:20:13,178 --> 00:20:15,078
WELL, ABOUT 27 YEARS AGO,       

467
00:20:15,147 --> 00:20:18,915
A CONSTRUCTION MANAGER CAME INTO
MY NEWSPAPER,<i> THE LAKOTA TIMES,</i> 

468
00:20:18,984 --> 00:20:20,550
AND HE HAD THIS WITH HIM.       

469
00:20:20,619 --> 00:20:22,586
ONE OF HIS EMPLOYEES,           
A LAKOTA MAN,                   

470
00:20:22,654 --> 00:20:24,821
HAD PUT IT IN HOCK              
AND SAID HE COULD HAVE IT       

471
00:20:24,890 --> 00:20:26,923
IF HE WENT DOWN                 
AND TOOK IT OUT OF PAWN.        

472
00:20:26,992 --> 00:20:29,626
SO HE BROUGHT IT DOWN           
TO MY NEWSPAPER.                

473
00:20:29,695 --> 00:20:32,996
ALONG WITH THAT WAS THIS LETTER 
WHICH IS DATED 1904.            

474
00:20:33,065 --> 00:20:37,501
IT'S WRITTEN ENTIRELY           
IN THE VERY OLD LAKOTA LANGUAGE.

475
00:20:37,569 --> 00:20:41,204
IT SAYS THAT "TASUNKA WITKO,"   
WHICH MEANS CRAZY HORSE.        

476
00:20:41,273 --> 00:20:43,573
   WHAT DO YOU KNOW SPECIFICALLY
   ABOUT CRAZY HORSE?           

477
00:20:43,642 --> 00:20:46,776
CRAZY HORSE WAS REALLY          
ONE OF THE GREAT WARRIORS       

478
00:20:46,845 --> 00:20:48,545
OF THE LAKOTA.                  

479
00:20:48,614 --> 00:20:50,647
PEOPLE SAID THAT BULLETS        
COULDN'T HIT HIM.               

480
00:20:50,716 --> 00:20:53,483
ONE OF THE REASONS              
HE'S SO ADMIRED AND LOVED       

481
00:20:53,552 --> 00:20:57,120
BY THE LAKOTA PEOPLE TODAY      
IS HE WOULD NEVER SIGN A TREATY.

482
00:20:57,189 --> 00:21:00,190
HE NEVER SOLD OUT ANY LAND      
OR ANY OF HIS PEOPLE,           

483
00:21:00,259 --> 00:21:02,859
AND TO ME THAT'S                
HIGHLY ADMIRABLE.               

484
00:21:02,928 --> 00:21:06,196
<i> BUT WHAT CRAZY HORSE LOOKS LIKE</i>
   <i> HAS LONG BEEN A MYSTERY.</i>    

485
00:21:06,265 --> 00:21:08,732
     DO YOU KNOW OF ANY OTHER   
     PHOTOGRAPHS OF CRAZY HORSE?

486
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:10,267
I'VE NEVER SEEN ONE.            

487
00:21:10,335 --> 00:21:13,436
I'VE SEEN PHOTOGRAPHS           
THAT WERE DISPROVED,            

488
00:21:13,505 --> 00:21:14,971
THAT THAT'S NOT CRAZY HORSE,    

489
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:16,740
ALWAYS PROVED TO BE             
SOMEONE ELSE.                   

490
00:21:16,808 --> 00:21:18,808
I WOULD LIKE YOU                
TO FIND OUT VERY MUCH           

491
00:21:18,877 --> 00:21:22,312
WHETHER THIS IS INDEED          
A TRUE PICTURE OF CRAZY HORSE.  

492
00:21:22,381 --> 00:21:24,581
            [ ♪♪♪ ]             

493
00:21:30,622 --> 00:21:32,622
 <i> IT'S JUST AS TIM SUGGESTED.</i>   

494
00:21:32,691 --> 00:21:34,925
      <i> THERE ARE A NUMBER</i>       
      <i> OF DISPUTED IMAGES</i>       

495
00:21:34,993 --> 00:21:36,760
 <i> CLAIMING TO BE CRAZY HORSE.</i>   

496
00:21:36,828 --> 00:21:39,062
      <i> MOST OF THEM HAVE</i>        
    <i> PRETTY SHAKY STORIES,</i>      

497
00:21:39,131 --> 00:21:40,997
  <i> AND NONE RESEMBLE OUR GUY.</i>   

498
00:21:41,066 --> 00:21:43,300
   <i> THERE'S NOTHING OBVIOUS</i>     
      <i> TO SUGGEST OUR MAN</i>       

499
00:21:43,368 --> 00:21:45,068
   <i> IS EVEN A WARRIOR CHIEF,</i>    

500
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:47,604
        <i> NO WAR BONNET</i>          
   <i> OR ELABORATE DECORATION.</i>    

501
00:21:47,673 --> 00:21:49,839
   HE DOES HAVE A COLLAR ON     
     AND AN EAGLE FEATHER,      

502
00:21:49,908 --> 00:21:52,475
       BUT BESIDES THAT,        
 HE'S DRESSED PRETTY PLAINLY.   

503
00:21:52,544 --> 00:21:55,045
      <i> I'M TRYING TO TAKE</i>       
   <i> THE BACK OFF CAREFULLY.</i>     

504
00:21:55,113 --> 00:21:57,247
    <i> IT LOOKS LIKE THERE'S</i>      
     <i> MORE LAKOTA WRITING</i>       

505
00:21:57,316 --> 00:22:00,150
  <i> ALONG WITH THE DATE, 1875.</i>   

506
00:22:02,020 --> 00:22:03,687
   AH, NOW, THIS IS HELPFUL.    

507
00:22:03,755 --> 00:22:07,924
  <i> HERE AGAIN, "CRAZY HORSE"</i>    
  <i> AND "1875" IN HANDWRITING.</i>   

508
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:10,694
       <i> BUT THERE'S ALSO</i>        
 <i> A STAMPED NAME AND ADDRESS.</i>   

509
00:22:10,762 --> 00:22:16,199
"ALEX GARDNER, 921 PENNSYLVANIA 
   AVENUE, WASHINGTON, D.C."    

510
00:22:16,268 --> 00:22:18,168
   <i> LET ME DO SOME DIGGING.</i>     

511
00:22:18,236 --> 00:22:19,936
<i> THERE WAS AN ALEXANDER GARDNER</i> 

512
00:22:20,005 --> 00:22:21,571
     <i> WHO WAS A CELEBRATED</i>      
         <i> PHOTOGRAPHER</i>          

513
00:22:21,640 --> 00:22:23,073
     <i> IN THE 19th CENTURY.</i>      

514
00:22:23,141 --> 00:22:25,075
       <i> HE PHOTOGRAPHED</i>         
       <i> ABRAHAM LINCOLN.</i>        

515
00:22:25,143 --> 00:22:27,243
       <i> I'M NOT CERTAIN</i>         
  <i> THEY WERE THE SAME PERSON,</i>   

516
00:22:27,312 --> 00:22:29,879
    <i> BUT ALEXANDER GARDNER</i>      
   <i> WAS A SCOTTISH SOCIALIST</i>    

517
00:22:29,948 --> 00:22:31,948
  <i> WHO HAD GOTTEN INTERESTED</i>    
        <i> IN PHOTOGRAPHY</i>         

518
00:22:32,017 --> 00:22:34,351
         <i> AFTER SEEING</i>          
    <i> MATTHEW BRADY'S WORK.</i>      

519
00:22:34,419 --> 00:22:35,752
   <i> BRADY AND GARDNER BECAME</i>    

520
00:22:35,821 --> 00:22:38,688
      <i> THE TWO BEST KNOWN</i>       
<i> PHOTOGRAPHERS OF THE CIVIL WAR.</i>

521
00:22:38,757 --> 00:22:41,458
  <i> BUT IT SEEMS THAT A NUMBER</i>   
<i> OF GARDNER'S BATTLEFIELD IMAGES</i>

522
00:22:41,526 --> 00:22:43,760
         <i> FROM THE WAR</i>          
     <i> WERE CONTROVERSIAL.</i>       

523
00:22:43,829 --> 00:22:46,563
   HE ACTUALLY MOVED BODIES     
 ON THE CIVIL WAR BATTLEFIELDS  

524
00:22:46,631 --> 00:22:49,299
        TO BETTER SUIT          
    HIS PHOTOGRAPHIC NEEDS.     

525
00:22:49,367 --> 00:22:51,000
   <i> AND THIS IS INTERESTING:</i>    

526
00:22:51,069 --> 00:22:54,904
     <i> GARDNER TRAVELED TO</i>       
<i> THE LAKOTA TERRITORIES IN 1868</i> 

527
00:22:54,973 --> 00:22:58,141
  <i> TO PHOTOGRAPH NEGOTIATIONS</i>   
<i> BETWEEN NORTHERN PLAIN TRIBES</i>  

528
00:22:58,210 --> 00:22:59,509
     <i> AND THE GOVERNMENT.</i>       

529
00:22:59,578 --> 00:23:01,311
   <i> THE FORT LARAMIE TREATY</i>     
         <i> ESTABLISHED</i>           

530
00:23:01,379 --> 00:23:03,012
 <i> THE GREAT SIOUX RESERVATION</i>   

531
00:23:03,081 --> 00:23:05,315
<i> AND PROTECTED THE BLACK HILLS</i>  
       <i> FOR THE LAKOTA.</i>         

532
00:23:05,383 --> 00:23:09,119
  <i> IT'S POSSIBLE THAT THIS IS</i>   
<i> AN ALEXANDER GARDNER PHOTOGRAPH</i>

533
00:23:09,187 --> 00:23:11,454
     <i> AND THAT GARDNER MET</i>      
         <i> CRAZY HORSE,</i>          

534
00:23:11,523 --> 00:23:15,158
  <i> BUT THE DATE ON OUR PHOTO,</i>   
      <i> IF IT'S ACCURATE,</i>        

535
00:23:15,227 --> 00:23:17,894
     <i> IS SEVEN YEARS AFTER</i>      
     <i> GARDNER PHOTOGRAPHED</i>      

536
00:23:17,963 --> 00:23:19,529
     <i> THE LAKOTA TREATIES.</i>      

537
00:23:19,598 --> 00:23:21,965
    I THINK THE FIRST THING     
       THAT I NEED TO DO        

538
00:23:22,033 --> 00:23:25,034
     IS FIGURE OUT EXACTLY      
     WHAT THIS NOTE SAYS.       

539
00:23:25,103 --> 00:23:27,370
        <i> I'M HEADED TO</i>          
    <i> OGLALA LAKOTA COLLEGE</i>      

540
00:23:27,439 --> 00:23:28,872
        <i> IN RAPID CITY.</i>         

541
00:23:28,940 --> 00:23:32,041
 <i> LAKOTA LANGUAGE AND CULTURE</i>   
   <i> PROFESSOR WILMER MESTETH</i>    

542
00:23:32,110 --> 00:23:34,010
  <i> IS SKEPTICAL OF OUR IMAGE.</i>   

543
00:23:34,079 --> 00:23:37,013
 <i> HE EXPLAINS WHY CRAZY HORSE</i>   
    <i> REJECTED PHOTOGRAPHY.</i>      

544
00:23:37,082 --> 00:23:39,349
       IN ORAL HISTORY THEY SAID
       HE MADE A STATEMENT      

545
00:23:39,417 --> 00:23:42,152
          THAT THESE PHOTOGRAPHS
          WERE EVIL             

546
00:23:42,220 --> 00:23:45,021
     AND THAT ANYBODY           
     THAT TOOK THEIR PHOTOGRAPH,

547
00:23:45,090 --> 00:23:47,624
         THEIR SOUL WAS CAPTURED
         IN THE PICTURE.        

548
00:23:47,692 --> 00:23:50,827
   <i> CRAZY HORSE'S REJECTION</i>     
<i> OF THE WHITE MAN'S TECHNOLOGY</i>  

549
00:23:50,896 --> 00:23:54,330
<i> WAS PART OF HIS DEFENSE OF THE</i> 
 <i> BESIEGED LAKOTA WAY OF LIFE.</i>  

550
00:23:54,399 --> 00:23:56,866
       <i> THE 1868 TREATY</i>         
       <i> OF FORT LARAMIE</i>         

551
00:23:56,935 --> 00:23:59,502
  <i> HAD GUARANTEED THE LAKOTA</i>    
     <i> THEIR TRIBAL LANDS,</i>       

552
00:23:59,571 --> 00:24:03,006
  <i> BUT JUST SIX YEARS LATER,</i>    
<i> THE TREATY WOULD BE VIOLATED.</i>  

553
00:24:03,074 --> 00:24:05,875
         IN 1874,               
         THERE WAS AN EXPEDITION

554
00:24:05,944 --> 00:24:09,245
  THAT CAME DOWN INTO THE       
  BLACK HILLS IN SEARCH OF GOLD,

555
00:24:09,314 --> 00:24:11,447
          LED BY GENERAL CUSTER,

556
00:24:11,516 --> 00:24:13,883
          AND THEY DID FIND GOLD
          IN THE BLACK HILLS.   

557
00:24:13,952 --> 00:24:17,954
       <i> TWO YEARS LATER,</i>        
        <i> IN JUNE 1876,</i>          

558
00:24:18,023 --> 00:24:20,490
  <i> CRAZY HORSE HELPED DEFEAT</i>    
        <i> GENERAL CUSTER</i>         

559
00:24:20,559 --> 00:24:22,592
        <i> AT THE BATTLE</i>          
    <i> OF THE LITTLE BIGHORN.</i>     

560
00:24:22,661 --> 00:24:26,129
<i> IT WAS THE WORST U.S. MILITARY</i> 
  <i> DEFEAT OF THE INDIAN WARS.</i>   

561
00:24:26,197 --> 00:24:27,830
        <i> ALTHOUGH MANY</i>          
     <i> SIOUX CONTEMPORARIES</i>      

562
00:24:27,899 --> 00:24:29,332
      <i> WERE PHOTOGRAPHED,</i>       

563
00:24:29,401 --> 00:24:31,401
    <i> THE LAKOTA HAVE RELIED</i>     
       <i> ON ORAL HISTORY</i>         

564
00:24:31,469 --> 00:24:33,436
      <i> FOR A DESCRIPTION</i>        
       <i> OF CRAZY HORSE.</i>         

565
00:24:33,505 --> 00:24:36,739
               THEY SAID HE WAS 
               OF MEDIUM HEIGHT,

566
00:24:36,808 --> 00:24:42,211
   HIS HAIR WAS LIGHT IN COLOR, 
   AND HIS COMPLEXION WAS LIGHT.

567
00:24:42,280 --> 00:24:45,615
    AND HE HAD A MYSTERIOUS AURA
    ABOUT HIM.                  

568
00:24:45,684 --> 00:24:48,651
 THEY SAID YOU COULD ALMOST FEEL
 HIS PRESENCE AND HIS STRENGTH  

569
00:24:48,720 --> 00:24:50,420
              AS A POWERFUL MAN.

570
00:24:50,488 --> 00:24:53,589
THIS IS THE LETTER              
THAT CAME WITH THE PHOTOGRAPH.  

571
00:24:53,658 --> 00:24:55,725
WHAT DO YOU THINK?              

572
00:24:55,794 --> 00:24:59,362
      THIS LETTER IS WRITTEN    
      IN OLD LAKOTA ORTHOGRAPHY,

573
00:24:59,431 --> 00:25:00,863
             IN LAKOTA LANGUAGE.

574
00:25:00,932 --> 00:25:03,900
<i> WILMER TELLS ME THAT OLD LAKOTA</i>
<i> WAS USED FOR A HUNED YEARS,</i>    

575
00:25:03,969 --> 00:25:06,336
      <i> UNTIL ABOUT 1960.</i>        

576
00:25:06,404 --> 00:25:10,273
     [ reading in Lakota ]      

577
00:25:10,342 --> 00:25:14,677
   "THIS PHOTOGRAPH IS          
   A PHOTOGRAPH OF CRAZY HORSE."

578
00:25:14,746 --> 00:25:16,145
WHAT ELSE DOES IT SAY?          

579
00:25:16,214 --> 00:25:21,284
     [ reading in Lakota ]      

580
00:25:21,353 --> 00:25:24,253
    "THE WAY YOU WOULD RECOGNIZE
    THAT THIS IS HE             

581
00:25:24,322 --> 00:25:27,190
             IS THERE IS A SCAR 
             ON HIS LEFT CHEEK."

582
00:25:27,258 --> 00:25:29,492
IS IT TRUE THAT CRAZY HORSE     
HAD A SCAR?                     

583
00:25:29,561 --> 00:25:33,896
       YES, CRAZY HORSE WAS SHOT
       BY A MAN CALLED NO WATER 

584
00:25:33,965 --> 00:25:35,431
              IN A JEALOUS RAGE.

585
00:25:35,500 --> 00:25:37,700
     HE SHOT TO KILL CRAZY HORSE

586
00:25:37,769 --> 00:25:41,804
 BUT GRAZED HIM ON THE LEFT SIDE
 OF THE CHEEK.                  

587
00:25:41,873 --> 00:25:44,240
     <i> THE MAN ON THE PHOTO</i>      
    <i> IS FAVORING HIS RIGHT.</i>     

588
00:25:44,309 --> 00:25:47,110
<i> IF THERE'S A SCAR ON THE LEFT,</i> 
        <i> I CAN'T TELL.</i>          

589
00:25:47,178 --> 00:25:50,947
     THEN IT SAYS, "WE WERE WITH
     CRAZY HORSE WAY BACK THEN. 

590
00:25:51,015 --> 00:25:53,750
       THIS IS ME, DEWEY BEARD."

591
00:25:53,818 --> 00:25:55,518
      <i> WILMER THINKS THAT</i>       
         <i> DEWEY BEARD</i>           

592
00:25:55,587 --> 00:25:57,687
 <i> MAY HAVE DICTATED THE STORY</i>   
         <i> TO SOMEONE,</i>           

593
00:25:57,756 --> 00:26:00,723
   <i> POSSIBLY TO THIS B.B.E.</i>     
    <i> SIGNED AT THE BOTTOM.</i>      

594
00:26:00,792 --> 00:26:02,325
AND WHO WAS DEWEY BEARD?        

595
00:26:02,394 --> 00:26:04,594
           DEWEY BEARD WAS THERE
           AT THE LITTLE BIGHORN

596
00:26:04,662 --> 00:26:06,295
     AT THE AGE OF 10 YEARS OLD.

597
00:26:06,364 --> 00:26:08,030
AND POSSIBLY KNEW               
CRAZY HORSE.                    

598
00:26:08,099 --> 00:26:11,033
     I'M PRETTY SURE THIS PERSON
     KNEW CRAZY HORSE, YES.     

599
00:26:11,102 --> 00:26:13,469
IN YOUR OPINION, DO YOU THINK   
THERE'S ANY POSSIBILITY         

600
00:26:13,538 --> 00:26:14,871
THAT THIS COULD BE              
CRAZY HORSE?                    

601
00:26:14,939 --> 00:26:16,672
               I DON'T THINK SO.

602
00:26:16,741 --> 00:26:21,310
  THIS PERSON IN THIS PHOTOGRAPH
  IS OF DARKER COMPLEXION.      

603
00:26:21,379 --> 00:26:23,946
          CRAZY HORSE HIMSELF   
          WAS LIGHT-COMPLECTED. 

604
00:26:24,015 --> 00:26:25,715
      <i> I'M NOT SURE WHAT</i>        
       <i> TO MAKE OF THIS.</i>        

605
00:26:25,784 --> 00:26:27,717
    <i> WILMER THINKS THE NOTE</i>     
        <i> IS LEGITIMATE.</i>         

606
00:26:27,786 --> 00:26:30,753
   <i> STILL, HISTORY'S VERDICT</i>    
      <i> STANDS IN OUR WAY.</i>       

607
00:26:30,822 --> 00:26:34,590
NOBODY'S EVER PRODUCED A        
PHOTOGRAPH OF CRAZY HORSE, EVER.

608
00:26:38,096 --> 00:26:40,696
   <i> WILMER SUGGESTED I VISIT</i>    
   <i> THE CRAZY HORSE MEMORIAL</i>    

609
00:26:40,765 --> 00:26:42,465
     <i> IN THE BLACK HILLS.</i>       

610
00:26:42,534 --> 00:26:45,768
 <i> SCULPTOR KORCZAK ZIOLKOWSKI</i>   
  <i> BEGAN THE MASSIVE CARVING</i>    

611
00:26:45,837 --> 00:26:50,439
       <i> IN THE 1940s...</i>         

612
00:26:50,508 --> 00:26:53,109
     <i> AND TODAY IT REMAINS</i>      
     <i> THE WORLD'S LARGEST</i>       

613
00:26:53,178 --> 00:26:55,611
      <i> MOUNTAIN SCULPTURE</i>       
         <i> IN PROGRESS.</i>          

614
00:26:55,680 --> 00:27:00,583
<i> THE MONUMENT IS A TESTAMENT TO</i> 
<i> THE IMPORTANCE OF HIS MEMORY,</i>  

615
00:27:00,652 --> 00:27:04,153
<i> BUT WHERE IS THE PHYSICAL MODEL</i>
    <i> FOR THE MASSIVE FACE?</i>      

616
00:27:04,222 --> 00:27:06,956
      <i> DOUG WAR EAGLE IS</i>        
   <i> CRAZY HORSE'S GRANDSON.</i>     

617
00:27:07,025 --> 00:27:08,424
     HOW WAS THE MONUMENT BUILT?

618
00:27:08,493 --> 00:27:10,193
          I MEAN, HOW DO WE KNOW
          WHAT HE LOOKS LIKE?   

619
00:27:10,261 --> 00:27:13,196
IT'S JUST THE CLOSEST REPLICA   
OF HIM.                         

620
00:27:13,264 --> 00:27:16,365
THERE NEVER WAS A PHOTO         
EVER TAKEN OF OUR GRANDFATHER.  

621
00:27:16,434 --> 00:27:19,502
<i> HE SAYS THE MONUMENT REPRESENTS</i>
     <i> CRAZY HORSE'S SPIRIT</i>      

622
00:27:19,571 --> 00:27:21,704
 <i> RATHER THAN HIS EXACT IMAGE.</i>  

623
00:27:21,773 --> 00:27:25,141
 <i> WHEN I SHOW DOUG OUR PHOTO,</i>   
  <i> RIGHT AWAY HE'S SKEPTICAL.</i>   

624
00:27:25,210 --> 00:27:28,244
THIS MAN HAS AN EAGLE FEATHER   
IN HIS HAIR.                    

625
00:27:28,313 --> 00:27:31,581
OUR GRANDFATHER NEVER WORE      
AN EAGLE FEATHER IN HIS HAIR.   

626
00:27:31,649 --> 00:27:35,651
OUR GRANDPA WEARS               
THE RED-TAILED HAWK FEATHER     

627
00:27:35,720 --> 00:27:37,520
WITH THE BUFFALO BONE.          

628
00:27:37,589 --> 00:27:39,155
   <i> DOUG'S BROUGHT SOMETHING</i>    
          <i> TO SHOW ME</i>           

629
00:27:39,224 --> 00:27:41,557
 <i> THAT FEW OUTSIDE HIS FAMILY</i>   
          <i> HAVE SEEN.</i>           

630
00:27:41,626 --> 00:27:44,794
I'VE BROUGHT TWO SKETCHES       
OF OUR GRANDFATHER'S.           

631
00:27:44,862 --> 00:27:48,464
THE FIRST ONE IS WAGLULA,       
OLD MAN CRAZY HORSE.            

632
00:27:48,533 --> 00:27:50,299
     <i> HE SAYS THE WARRIOR</i>       
         <i> CRAZY HORSE</i>           

633
00:27:50,368 --> 00:27:52,969
  <i> WAS ACTUALLY THE THIRD MAN</i>   
     <i> TO CARRY THAT NAME.</i>       

634
00:27:53,037 --> 00:27:55,204
        <i> IN ACCORDANCE</i>          
    <i> WITH LAKOTA TRADITION,</i>     

635
00:27:55,273 --> 00:27:59,041
<i> CRAZY HORSE INHERITED THE NAME</i> 
  <i> FROM THIS MAN, HIS FATHER,</i>   

636
00:27:59,110 --> 00:28:00,810
  <i> WHEN HE BECAME A WARRIOR.</i>    

637
00:28:00,878 --> 00:28:05,281
AND THE OTHER SKETCH I HAVE HERE
IS OF THE WARRIOR.              

638
00:28:05,350 --> 00:28:08,551
  <i> IT WAS SKETCHED LONG AFTER</i>   
      <i> HIS DEATH IN 1934,</i>       

639
00:28:08,620 --> 00:28:10,686
      <i> WHEN CRAZY HORSE'S</i>       
        <i> YOUNGER SISTER</i>         

640
00:28:10,755 --> 00:28:13,522
   <i> DESCRIBED HIS APPEARANCE</i>    
    <i> TO A FORENSIC ARTIST.</i>      

641
00:28:13,591 --> 00:28:16,092
    <i> THE LIKENESS TRIGGERED</i>     
    <i> AN EMOTIONAL REACTION.</i>     

642
00:28:16,160 --> 00:28:19,095
SHE CRIED, BECAUSE SHE SAID     
THAT'S THE CLOSEST LIKENESS     

643
00:28:19,163 --> 00:28:22,131
THAT YOU WILL EVER HAVE         
OF HIM.                         

644
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:23,833
                 IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

645
00:28:23,901 --> 00:28:27,203
      WELL, HE CERTAINLY DOESN'T
      LOOK LIKE OUR PHOTOGRAPH. 

646
00:28:27,271 --> 00:28:29,605
     SO IT HAS THE TWO FEATHERS,
     THE LONG, FLOWING HAIR,    

647
00:28:29,674 --> 00:28:31,974
                AND A LITTLE BIT
                OF A SCAR.      

648
00:28:32,043 --> 00:28:33,709
THAT'S THE CLOSEST              
WE'LL EVER GET                  

649
00:28:33,778 --> 00:28:35,578
OF OUR GRANDFATHER,             
THE WARRIOR,                    

650
00:28:35,647 --> 00:28:37,947
THE ONE THAT FOUGHT             
THE BATTLE OF LITTLE BIGHORN.   

651
00:28:38,016 --> 00:28:40,783
 <i> DOUG IS CONVINCED OUR IMAGE</i>   
      <i> ISN'T CRAZY HORSE.</i>       

652
00:28:40,852 --> 00:28:42,952
       <i> BUT THIS SKETCH</i>         
     <i> WAS MADE BY SOMEONE</i>       

653
00:28:43,021 --> 00:28:47,323
  <i> WHO NEVER MET CRAZAZY HORSE,</i> 
  <i> SIX DECADES AFTER HE DIED.</i>   

654
00:28:47,392 --> 00:28:50,059
     <i> I'M TAKING THE IMAGE</i>      
     <i> TO THE SMITHSONIAN,</i>       

655
00:28:50,128 --> 00:28:52,428
         <i> WHICH HOUSES</i>          
 <i> THE WORLD'S LARGEST ARCHIVE</i>   

656
00:28:52,497 --> 00:28:54,630
<i> OF NATIVE-AMERICAN PHOTOGRAPHS.</i>

657
00:28:54,699 --> 00:28:57,199
   <i> I WANT TO SHOW IT TO ONE</i>    
<i> OF THE SMITHSONIAN'S CURATORS.</i> 

658
00:28:57,268 --> 00:28:58,901
          <i> BUT FIRST,</i>           
   <i> BECAUSE THERE HAVE BEEN</i>     

659
00:28:58,970 --> 00:29:00,803
          <i> MANY BOGUS</i>           
    <i> CRAZY HORSE PICTURES,</i>      

660
00:29:00,872 --> 00:29:03,039
       <i> WHILE I'M HERE,</i>         
    <i> I ALSO WANT TO SHOW IT</i>     

661
00:29:03,107 --> 00:29:05,674
    <i> TO STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER</i>      
        <i> DON HURLBURT.</i>          

662
00:29:05,743 --> 00:29:08,077
WELCOME TO THE DARKROOM.        

663
00:29:11,416 --> 00:29:12,782
                    WOW.        

664
00:29:12,850 --> 00:29:16,185
   OKAY, SO HERE'S MY PIECE,    
   AND ON THE BACK IT SAYS 1875.

665
00:29:16,254 --> 00:29:18,087
  I WAS WONDERING IF YOU THOUGHT
  IT WAS PERIOD.                

666
00:29:18,156 --> 00:29:19,822
IT DEFINITELY HAS               
CHARACTERISTICS                 

667
00:29:19,891 --> 00:29:21,557
FROM THAT TIME FRAME.           

668
00:29:21,626 --> 00:29:24,727
IT'S YELLOWING, IT'S GOT        
A GOOD GOLD TONE TO IT.         

669
00:29:24,796 --> 00:29:27,029
IT HAS THE SHININESS            
ON THE SURFACE OF THE PRINT     

670
00:29:27,098 --> 00:29:29,465
THAT A MODERN PRINT             
WOULD NOT HAVE                  

671
00:29:29,534 --> 00:29:31,066
BUT PRINTS OF THAT AGE DO.      

672
00:29:31,135 --> 00:29:34,136
    HOW WOULD A PRINT LIKE THIS 
    HAVE BEEN MADE IN THE 1870s?

673
00:29:34,205 --> 00:29:37,306
IT WAS DEFINITELY A MULTI-DAY,  
MULTI-STEP PROCESS              

674
00:29:37,375 --> 00:29:38,874
TO MAKE ONE OF THESE PRINTS.    

675
00:29:38,943 --> 00:29:42,278
THESE GUYS DID A LOT OF WORK    
TO GET THESE PHOTOGRAPHS.       

676
00:29:42,346 --> 00:29:44,380
THESE PRINTS CAME               
FROM GLASS PLATE NEGATIVES      

677
00:29:44,449 --> 00:29:47,683
THAT WERE MADE, PRODUCED FROM   
ABOUT THE 1850s TO 1880s.       

678
00:29:47,752 --> 00:29:49,251
WELL, I CAN SHOW YOU.           

679
00:29:49,320 --> 00:29:52,054
<i> THE INVENTION OF GLASS PLATES</i>  
<i> MEANT THAT FOR THE FIRST TIME,</i> 

680
00:29:52,123 --> 00:29:54,990
  <i> PHOTOGRAPHERS LIKE GARDNER</i>   
  <i> HAD A PHOTOGRAPHIC MEDIUM</i>    

681
00:29:55,059 --> 00:29:57,760
      <i> FROM WHICH TO MAKE</i>       
 <i> UNLIMITED NUMBERS OF PRINTS.</i>  

682
00:29:57,829 --> 00:30:00,496
 <i> GLASS PLATES REVOLUTIONIZED</i>   
         <i> PHOTOGRAPHY.</i>          

683
00:30:00,565 --> 00:30:03,499
        NOW THAT I'VE CLEANED IT
        AND CHECKED IT,         

684
00:30:03,568 --> 00:30:06,735
         WE'RE GOING TO BRING IT
         OVER HERE, SET IT DOWN,

685
00:30:06,804 --> 00:30:10,239
GET A SHEET OF MODERN PAPER OUT,
BECAUSE WE DO NOT HAVE          

686
00:30:10,308 --> 00:30:13,475
        ANY OF THE ALBUMEN PAPER
        WITH US ANYMORE.        

687
00:30:13,544 --> 00:30:16,645
 <i> DON SAYS GARDNER, OR WHOEVER</i>  
     <i> TOOK THE PHOTOGRAPH,</i>      

688
00:30:16,714 --> 00:30:18,814
       <i> WOULD HAVE MADE</i>         
    <i> ALBUMEN SILVER PRINTS,</i>     

689
00:30:18,883 --> 00:30:20,983
        <i> WHICH EXPOSED</i>          
         <i> IN SUNLIGHT.</i>          

690
00:30:21,052 --> 00:30:23,219
     <i> TODAY, USING MODERN</i>       
         <i> PHOTO PAPER,</i>          

691
00:30:23,287 --> 00:30:26,322
  <i> DEVELOPING A PRINT IN THE</i>    
 <i> DARKROOM TAKES MERE MINUTES.</i>  

692
00:30:26,390 --> 00:30:27,923
                   THAT'S GREAT.

693
00:30:27,992 --> 00:30:30,726
 <i> I LEARN MORE ABOUT THE PRINT</i>  
    <i> FROM FORMER ARCHIVIST</i>      

694
00:30:30,795 --> 00:30:33,929
  <i> AND SMITHSONIAN VOLUNTEER</i>    
        <i> PAULA FLEMING.</i>         

695
00:30:33,998 --> 00:30:37,499
<i> SHE SAYS THE IMAGE WAS ALMOST</i>  
  <i> CERTAINLY TAKEN BY GARDNER</i>   

696
00:30:37,568 --> 00:30:40,135
         <i> NOT OUT WEST</i>          
    <i> BUT ON THE EAST COAST</i>      

697
00:30:40,204 --> 00:30:42,638
        <i> AT THE ADDRESS</i>         
<i> ON THE BACK OF OUR PHOTOGRAPH.</i> 

698
00:30:42,707 --> 00:30:44,974
HE HAD A STUDIO                 
IN WASHINGTON, D.C.,            

699
00:30:45,042 --> 00:30:47,543
AND HE TOOK MOST OF HIS         
INDIAN PORTRAITS THERE.         

700
00:30:47,612 --> 00:30:49,545
     WELL, WHAT WOULD BRING THEM
     TO WASHINGTON, D.C.?       

701
00:30:49,614 --> 00:30:51,647
AFTER THE CIVIL WAR,            
THE UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT    

702
00:30:51,716 --> 00:30:54,383
RENEWED ITS EFFORTS             
TO DEAL WITH THE INDIANS        

703
00:30:54,452 --> 00:30:57,653
TO RESOLVE ISSUES OF LAND       
ACQUISITION AND ANNUITIES.      

704
00:30:57,722 --> 00:30:59,888
     <i> PAULA SAYS HUNDREDS</i>       
     <i> OF AMERICAN INDIANS</i>       

705
00:30:59,957 --> 00:31:03,025
  <i> WERE INVITED TO WASHINGTON</i>   
    <i> AS TRIBAL DELEGATIONS.</i>     

706
00:31:03,094 --> 00:31:05,094
THE GOVERNMENT WANTED           
TO SHOW THE INDIANS             

707
00:31:05,162 --> 00:31:06,829
THE BENEFITS OF CIVILIZATION,   

708
00:31:06,897 --> 00:31:09,431
SO THEY TOOK THEM ON TRAINS     
AND THEY TOOK THEM TO BIG CITIES

709
00:31:09,500 --> 00:31:12,334
TO SHOW THEM WHAT IT WAS LIKE   
TO BE CIVILIZED.                

710
00:31:12,403 --> 00:31:14,770
       <i> ON THE SURFACE,</i>         
    <i> THE WASHINGTON VISITS</i>      

711
00:31:14,839 --> 00:31:17,172
  <i> WERE EFFORTS TO PEACEFULLY</i>   
    <i> RESOLVE LAND DISPUTES</i>      

712
00:31:17,241 --> 00:31:18,974
       <i> AND DEMONSTRATE</i>         
       <i> THAT THE INDIANS</i>        

713
00:31:19,043 --> 00:31:20,809
      <i> WERE BEING TREATED</i>       
        <i> RESPECTFULLY,</i>          

714
00:31:20,878 --> 00:31:23,612
  <i> BUT PAULA SAYS THE VISITS</i>    
    <i> OFTEN INCLUDED A STOP</i>      

715
00:31:23,681 --> 00:31:25,581
<i> WHICH HAD A POLITICAL AGENDA.</i>  

716
00:31:25,650 --> 00:31:27,783
       THEY WOULD ALSO TAKE THEM
       TO THE ARSENAL           

717
00:31:27,852 --> 00:31:29,618
            AND THEY'D SHOW THEM
            STOCKPILES          

718
00:31:29,687 --> 00:31:32,087
      OF WEAPONS AND CANNONBALLS

719
00:31:32,156 --> 00:31:35,824
    AND THEY WOULD HAVE DISPLAYS
    OF MILITARY MIGHT.          

720
00:31:35,893 --> 00:31:37,493
           THE GOVERNMENT WANTED
           TO SHOW THEM         

721
00:31:37,561 --> 00:31:39,795
     THAT IT WAS ACTUALLY FUTILE
     TO FIGHT FOR THEIR LANDS.  

722
00:31:39,864 --> 00:31:41,063
THEY WERE GOING TO LOSE?        

723
00:31:41,132 --> 00:31:42,398
        THEY WERE GOING TO LOSE.

724
00:31:42,466 --> 00:31:44,299
    <i> CRAZY HORSE'S GRANDSON</i>     
         <i> HAD TOLD ME</i>           

725
00:31:44,368 --> 00:31:46,335
      <i> THAT THE CLOTHING</i>        
 <i> AND DECORATION IN OUR IMAGE</i>   

726
00:31:46,404 --> 00:31:48,404
       <i> WAS NOT TYPICAL</i>         
       <i> FOR THE WARRIOR.</i>        

727
00:31:48,472 --> 00:31:51,607
  <i> BUT PAULA SAYS NOT ALL THE</i>   
<i> PHOTOGRAPHS TAKEN IN WASHINGTON</i>

728
00:31:51,676 --> 00:31:53,442
<i> WERE WHAT THEY APPEARED TO BE.</i> 

729
00:31:53,511 --> 00:31:55,778
SOME PHOTOGRAPHERS              
ACTUALLY KEPT PROPS             

730
00:31:55,846 --> 00:31:58,080
TO MAKE SURE THAT THE INDIANS   
LOOKED EXOTIC ENOUGH,           

731
00:31:58,149 --> 00:32:00,416
AND SOMETIMES THEY PUT          
THE IMPROPER COSTUMES           

732
00:32:00,484 --> 00:32:02,651
ON THE WRONG CULTURES.          

733
00:32:02,720 --> 00:32:04,920
 <i> PAULA HAS A SURPRISE FOR ME.</i>  

734
00:32:04,989 --> 00:32:07,222
WITH THOUSANDS OF PHOTOGRAPHS   
IN THE ARCHIVES,                

735
00:32:07,291 --> 00:32:09,591
IT CAN BE A LITTLE DAUNTING     
IF YOU DON'T HAVE A NAME.       

736
00:32:09,660 --> 00:32:11,960
BUT I DID A LITTLE BIT          
OF RESEARCH, AND COME HERE,     

737
00:32:12,029 --> 00:32:13,862
I'VE GOT SOMETHING              
TO SHOW YOU.                    

738
00:32:13,931 --> 00:32:15,564
        WOW!                    

739
00:32:15,633 --> 00:32:17,066
 <i> IT'S A GLASS PLATE NEGATIVE,</i>  

740
00:32:17,134 --> 00:32:19,068
      <i> JUST LIKE THE ONE</i>        
        <i> DON SHOWED ME.</i>         

741
00:32:19,136 --> 00:32:20,436
IT'S THE EXACT SAME IMAGE.      

742
00:32:20,504 --> 00:32:21,704
                        SURE IS.

743
00:32:21,772 --> 00:32:24,273
          THIS NEGATIVE WAS USED
          TO PRINT THAT IMAGE.  

744
00:32:24,341 --> 00:32:25,841
IS IT CRAZY HORSE?              

745
00:32:25,910 --> 00:32:28,777
   <i> WHAT PAULA TELLS ME NEXT</i>    
       <i> CLOSES THE CASE.</i>        

746
00:32:28,846 --> 00:32:30,913
    WELL, TIM, IT WAS           
    AN INCREDIBLE INVESTIGATION.

747
00:32:30,981 --> 00:32:34,450
<i> I TELL HIM HE HAS AN AUTHENTIC</i> 
   <i> ALEXANDER GARDNER PHOTO,</i>    

748
00:32:34,518 --> 00:32:36,318
     <i> ONE OF THE NATION'S</i>       
       <i> MOST CELEBRATED</i>         

749
00:32:36,387 --> 00:32:37,786
    <i> PERIOD PHOTOGRAPHERS.</i>      

750
00:32:37,855 --> 00:32:40,322
      THERE ARE A LOT OF EXPERTS
      THAT DON'T BELIEVE        

751
00:32:40,391 --> 00:32:42,558
          THAT CRAZY HORSE      
          WAS EVER PHOTOGRAPHED,

752
00:32:42,626 --> 00:32:44,526
               AND THAT MADE IT 
               REALLY DIFFICULT.

753
00:32:44,595 --> 00:32:46,462
          FINALLY, THOUGH,      
          I WAS ABLE TO IDENTIFY

754
00:32:46,530 --> 00:32:48,197
      THE MAN IN YOUR PHOTOGRAPH

755
00:32:48,265 --> 00:32:50,165
            BY TRAVELING        
            TO WASHINGTON, D.C.,

756
00:32:50,234 --> 00:32:53,202
                JUST LIKE HE DID
                150 YEARS AGO.  

757
00:32:53,270 --> 00:32:55,838
THERE WAS AN ENGLISHMAN BY THE  
NAME OF WILLIAM HENRY BLACKMORE,

758
00:32:55,906 --> 00:32:58,040
     AND HE COMMISSIONED GARDNER
     TO PHOTOGRAPH              

759
00:32:58,109 --> 00:32:59,675
     THE DELEGATIONS OF INDIANS.

760
00:32:59,743 --> 00:33:01,610
           AND HE ALSO PUBLISHED
           THE IMAGES.          

761
00:33:01,679 --> 00:33:03,412
THAT'S OUR GUY.                 

762
00:33:03,481 --> 00:33:05,681
       THE MAN IN THE PHOTOGRAPH
       IS VUA-SHA-PEH,          

763
00:33:05,749 --> 00:33:07,516
              WHOSE ENGLISH NAME
              IS STABBER,       

764
00:33:07,585 --> 00:33:10,886
   AND HE WAS AN OGLALA LAKOTA  
   WHO CAME TO WASHINGTON, D.C.,

765
00:33:10,955 --> 00:33:13,288
                WITH RED CLOUD  
                ON A DELEGATION.

766
00:33:13,357 --> 00:33:15,290
 <i> THE MAN IN THIS PHOTOGRAPHED</i>  
        <i> HAD WITNESSED</i>          

767
00:33:15,359 --> 00:33:17,559
       <i> ONE OF THE LAST</i>         
    <i> PEACEFUL NEGOTIATIONS</i>      

768
00:33:17,628 --> 00:33:19,895
      <i> BETWEEN THE LAKOTA</i>       
  <i> AND THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT</i>   

769
00:33:19,964 --> 00:33:22,464
  <i> BEFORE GOLD WAS DISCOVERED</i>   
     <i> IN THE BLACK HILLS.</i>       

770
00:33:22,533 --> 00:33:25,567
        HE WAS AN IMPORTANT PART
        OF LAKOTA HISTORY.      

771
00:33:25,636 --> 00:33:28,103
     I THINK IT'S GREAT         
     THAT WE KNOW WHO HE IS NOW.

772
00:33:28,172 --> 00:33:29,972
   <i> VUA-SHA-PEH HAD TRAVELED</i>    
        <i> TO WASHINGTON</i>          

773
00:33:30,040 --> 00:33:32,474
        <i> WITH RED CLOUD</i>         
  <i> AND THE LAKOTA DELEGATION.</i>   

774
00:33:32,543 --> 00:33:36,011
   <i> IN CONTRAST, CRAZY HORSE</i>    
      <i> REJECTED DIPLOMACY</i>       

775
00:33:36,080 --> 00:33:39,581
<i> AND DEFENDED LAKOTA TRADITIONS</i> 
   <i> AS A WARRIOR TO THE END.</i>    

776
00:33:39,650 --> 00:33:42,050
  EXPERTS SAY THAT HE NEVER WENT
  TO WASHINGTON;                

777
00:33:42,119 --> 00:33:44,486
         HE STAYED ON HIS LAND  
         TO FIGHT FOR HIS PEOPLE

778
00:33:44,555 --> 00:33:46,488
              AND TO FIGHT      
              THE U.S. MILITARY.

779
00:33:46,557 --> 00:33:48,524
I'M A GREAT ADMIRER             
OF CRAZY HORSE,                 

780
00:33:48,592 --> 00:33:51,226
AND I REALLY HOPED              
THAT THIS WAS HIM.              

781
00:33:51,295 --> 00:33:56,932
WELL, I GUESS WE'LL NEVER KNOW  
WHAT CRAZY HORSE LOOKED LIKE.   

782
00:33:57,001 --> 00:33:59,401
I HOPE THAT I CAN TAKE          
THE PHOTOGRAPH                  

783
00:33:59,470 --> 00:34:01,370
AND FIND HIS DESCENDANTS        

784
00:34:01,438 --> 00:34:03,605
AND PASS THE PHOTOGRAPH         
DOWN TO THEM.                   

785
00:34:03,674 --> 00:34:05,641
WE THANK YOU FOR COMING         
ALL THE WAY OUT HERE            

786
00:34:05,709 --> 00:34:08,277
TO GIVE US THE NEWS.            

787
00:34:08,345 --> 00:34:10,779
      <i> AFTER HIS VICTORY</i>        
    <i> AT THE LITTLE BIGHORN,</i>     

788
00:34:10,848 --> 00:34:14,483
    <i> CRAZY HORSE FOUGHT ON</i>      
  <i> UNTIL THE SPRING OF 1877.</i>    

789
00:34:14,551 --> 00:34:17,319
  <i> THEN, HIS PEOPLE WEAKENED</i>    
      <i> BY WAR AND HUNGER,</i>       

790
00:34:17,388 --> 00:34:20,622
        <i> HE SURRENDERED</i>         
 <i> AT CAMP ROBINSON, NEBRASKA.</i>   

791
00:34:20,691 --> 00:34:23,592
    <i> ON SEPTEMBER 5, 1877,</i>      

792
00:34:23,661 --> 00:34:26,295
 <i> HE WAS ARRESTED AND BROUGHT</i>   
    <i> INTO THE GUARD HOUSE.</i>      

793
00:34:26,363 --> 00:34:28,463
       <i> REALIZING HE WAS</i>        
    <i> ABOUT TO BE LOCKED UP,</i>     

794
00:34:28,532 --> 00:34:30,432
    <i> CRAZY HORSE STRUGGLED</i>      
       <i> AND WAS STABBED</i>         

795
00:34:30,501 --> 00:34:32,501
         <i> BY A SOLDIER</i>          
       <i> WITH A BAYONET.</i>         

796
00:34:32,569 --> 00:34:34,937
   <i> HE DIED LATE THAT NIGHT,</i>    
       <i> AND SOON AFTER,</i>         

797
00:34:35,005 --> 00:34:37,572
    <i> HIS BODY WAS RETURNED</i>      
   <i> TO HIS ELDERLY PARENTS.</i>     

798
00:34:37,641 --> 00:34:40,709
    <i> TO THIS DAY, HIS FINAL</i>     
   <i> BURIAL PLACE IS UNKNOWN,</i>    

799
00:34:40,778 --> 00:34:44,546
   <i> BUT HIS SPIRIT LIVES ON</i>     
     <i> IN THE BLACK HILLS.</i>       

800
00:34:48,385 --> 00:34:50,552
      REPATRIATION RAISES       
        COMPLEX ISSUES          

801
00:34:50,621 --> 00:34:53,221
    ABOUT CULTURAL HERITAGE     
       AND WHO OWNS IT.         

802
00:34:53,290 --> 00:34:56,758
   TODAY, LITERALLY MILLIONS    
 OF AMERICAN INDIAN ARTIFACTS   

803
00:34:56,827 --> 00:35:00,696
ARE HOUSED IN NON-NATIVE MUSEUMS
   AND PRIVATE COLLECTIONS.     

804
00:35:00,764 --> 00:35:04,499
  MANY OF THESE OBJECTS, LIKE   
 TOOLS, WEAPONS, AND CLOTHES,   

805
00:35:04,568 --> 00:35:07,336
     WERE ACQUIRED THROUGH      
    PERFECTLY LEGAL MEANS.      

806
00:35:07,404 --> 00:35:11,206
 OTHERS, HOWEVER, WERE BOUGHT   
    FOR PENNIES OR STOLEN.      

807
00:35:11,275 --> 00:35:13,575
    THE U.S. GOVERNMENT SAW     
   NOTHING WRONG WITH THIS,     

808
00:35:13,644 --> 00:35:16,111
  SINCE ITS OFFICIAL POSITION   
         ON THE TRIBES          

809
00:35:16,180 --> 00:35:19,681
 WAS TO TRY TO ASSIMILATE THEM  
     INTO THE MAINSTREAM.       

810
00:35:19,750 --> 00:35:22,751
      BUT NATIVE PEOPLES        
      ARE STILL WITH US,        

811
00:35:22,820 --> 00:35:26,388
AND SOME HAVE BEGUN TO ASK FOR  
       -- EVEN DEMAND --        

812
00:35:26,457 --> 00:35:28,957
     THEIR MOST IMPORTANT       
        ARTIFACTS BACK.         

813
00:35:29,026 --> 00:35:32,360
SO IN 1990, THE U.S. GOVERNMENT 
        SIGNED INTO LAW         

814
00:35:32,429 --> 00:35:34,930
      THE NATIVE AMERICAN       
       GRAVE PROTECTION         

815
00:35:34,998 --> 00:35:38,133
     AND REPATRIATION ACT,      
          OR NAGPRA.            

816
00:35:38,202 --> 00:35:41,269
        NAGPRA REQUIRES         
FEDERALLY FUNDED ORGANIZATIONS  

817
00:35:41,338 --> 00:35:45,307
TO RETURN SKELETONS AND OBJECTS 
     OF CULTURAL PATRIMONY      

818
00:35:45,375 --> 00:35:46,942
   TO TRIBAL REPRESENTATIVES    

819
00:35:47,010 --> 00:35:49,144
        IF THEY FOLLOW          
    THE CORRECT PROCEDURES.     

820
00:35:49,213 --> 00:35:52,647
    NAGPRA ONLY APPLIES TO      
FEDERALLY FUNDED ORGANIZATIONS. 

821
00:35:52,716 --> 00:35:55,183
      PRIVATE COLLECTIONS       
       OR MUSEUMS ABROAD        

822
00:35:55,252 --> 00:35:57,619
       DON'T FALL UNDER         
       ITS JURISDICTION.        

823
00:35:57,688 --> 00:36:00,789
   DESPITE THESE CHALLENGES,    
  BOTH THE TRIBES AND MUSEUMS   

824
00:36:00,858 --> 00:36:03,725
 SEE NAGPRA AS A STEP FORWARD.  

825
00:36:07,364 --> 00:36:09,498
             Wes:               
  <i> IN AN ENCORE PRESENTATION,</i>   

826
00:36:09,566 --> 00:36:12,968
<i> OUR FINAL STORY TURNS THE PAGES</i>
     <i> OF A LONG-LOST DIARY</i>      

827
00:36:13,036 --> 00:36:16,538
     <i> FROM A WORLD WAR II</i>       
        <i> BOMBER PILOT.</i>          

828
00:36:16,607 --> 00:36:19,608
      <i> DECEMBER 13, 1943:</i>       

829
00:36:19,676 --> 00:36:23,111
   <i> THE U.S. ARMY AIR FORCE</i>     
       <i> 445th BOMB GROUP</i>        

830
00:36:23,180 --> 00:36:24,880
   <i> ATTACKS ENEMY SHIPYARDS</i>     

831
00:36:24,948 --> 00:36:27,415
      <i> BENEATH THE SKIES</i>        
      <i> OF KIEL, GERMANY.</i>        

832
00:36:27,484 --> 00:36:31,052
       <i> IT'S THEIR FIRST</i>        
   <i> OF 280 AIR-RAID MISSIONS</i>    

833
00:36:31,121 --> 00:36:34,856
     <i> INSIDE A NEW BOMBER</i>       
  <i> CALLED THE B-24 LIBERATOR.</i>   

834
00:36:34,925 --> 00:36:38,093
        <i> THE BOMBER IS</i>          
   <i> THE ALLIES' GREAT HOPE,</i>     

835
00:36:38,162 --> 00:36:41,263
   <i> FLYING FARTHER, LONGER,</i>     
   <i> AND CARRYING MORE BOMBS</i>     

836
00:36:41,331 --> 00:36:43,165
      <i> DEEP INTO HITLER'S</i>       
           <i> GERMANY.</i>            

837
00:36:43,233 --> 00:36:45,800
  <i> NOT A SINGLE PLANE IS LOST</i>   
       <i> ON THIS MISSION,</i>        

838
00:36:45,869 --> 00:36:50,305
  <i> BUT THE 445th WILL RARELY</i>    
      <i> BE SO LUCKY AGAIN.</i>       

839
00:36:50,374 --> 00:36:53,508
  <i> THE LIBERATOR EARNS ITSELF</i>   
<i> ANOTHER MORE OMINOUS NICKNAME:</i> 

840
00:36:53,577 --> 00:36:55,377
      <i> THE FLYING COFFIN,</i>       

841
00:36:55,445 --> 00:36:58,914
<i> DUE TO THE HIGH CASUALTY RATE</i>  
      <i> AMONG B-24 PILOTS.</i>       

842
00:36:58,982 --> 00:37:02,417
   <i> WHY WERE THESE MISSIONS</i>     
          <i> SO DEADLY,</i>           

843
00:37:02,486 --> 00:37:06,021
<i> AND WHAT CONVINCED THEIR CREW</i>  
<i> TO ACCEPT SUCH TERRIBLE ODDS?</i>  

844
00:37:09,359 --> 00:37:11,826
  <i> SIXTY YEARS AFTER THE LAST</i>   
      <i> OF THOSE MISSIONS,</i>       

845
00:37:11,895 --> 00:37:14,563
         <i> JIM CHAPMAN</i>           
<i> OF LEXINGTON, NORTH CAROLINA,</i>  

846
00:37:14,631 --> 00:37:17,299
 <i> HAS A DIARY THAT MAY REVEAL</i>   
       <i> NEW INFORMATION</i>         

847
00:37:17,367 --> 00:37:21,636
  <i> ABOUT THESE PLANES AND MEN</i>   
   <i> WHO HELD HITLER AT BAY.</i>     

848
00:37:21,705 --> 00:37:25,173
        <i> I'M WES COWAN,</i>         
 <i> AND I'M HEADING TO MEET JIM.</i>  

849
00:37:25,242 --> 00:37:26,708
    NICE TO MEET YOU.           

850
00:37:26,777 --> 00:37:28,410
LET'S TAKE A LOOK               
AT THIS DIARY.                  

851
00:37:28,478 --> 00:37:30,478
             MY DAD BROUGHT THIS
             HOME WITH HIM      

852
00:37:30,547 --> 00:37:32,447
               AFTER HE FINISHED
               HIS TOUR OF DUTY 

853
00:37:32,516 --> 00:37:34,182
            DURING WORLD WAR II.

854
00:37:34,251 --> 00:37:36,551
AND THE OBVIOUS QUESTION        
TO ME IS,                       

855
00:37:36,620 --> 00:37:38,420
IT'S NOT YOUR DAD'S DIARY.      

856
00:37:38,488 --> 00:37:39,821
                 THAT'S CORRECT.

857
00:37:39,890 --> 00:37:43,458
   THE DIARY BELONGED TO HIS    
   CO-PILOT NAMED WILLIAM MORAN.

858
00:37:43,527 --> 00:37:46,227
          BOTH SERVED ON A B-24.

859
00:37:46,296 --> 00:37:49,464
     <i> BOTH MEN FLEW PLANES</i>      
   <i> IN THE 445th BOMB GROUP</i>     

860
00:37:49,533 --> 00:37:51,433
         <i> STATIONED IN</i>          
      <i> TIBENHAM, ENGLAND.</i>       

861
00:37:51,501 --> 00:37:53,201
HOW DID YOUR DAD                
GET IT?                         

862
00:37:53,270 --> 00:37:55,036
                WELL, THAT'S    
                A GOOD QUESTION.

863
00:37:55,105 --> 00:37:57,505
           I ACTUALLY DISCOVERED
           THE DIARY            

864
00:37:57,574 --> 00:38:00,075
        IN A BOX                
        OF MY FATHER'S MEMENTOS.

865
00:38:00,143 --> 00:38:03,745
    <i> HE DISCOVERED IT AFTER</i>     
<i> HIS FATHER DIED 20 YEARS AGO.</i>  

866
00:38:03,814 --> 00:38:05,413
CAN YOU READ ME                 
SOME ENTRIES?                   

867
00:38:05,482 --> 00:38:07,816
            YES, I'D BE GLAD TO.

868
00:38:07,884 --> 00:38:09,684
            "SURE DREADED GOING,

869
00:38:09,753 --> 00:38:12,854
       "ESPECIALLY AFTER I FOUND
       THE TARGET TO BE HAMBURG.

870
00:38:12,923 --> 00:38:15,557
            "FELT SURE          
            I WOULDN'T GET BACK.

871
00:38:15,625 --> 00:38:18,593
      "AT LEAST I KNOW NOW THAT 
      I'LL BE ABLE TO FACE DEATH

872
00:38:18,662 --> 00:38:20,628
            "WHEN MY TIME COMES.

873
00:38:20,697 --> 00:38:24,032
   "THE ONLY THING THAT I FEARED
   WAS LEAVING JAYNE.           

874
00:38:24,101 --> 00:38:26,801
      I ADORE HER EVERY BREATH."

875
00:38:26,870 --> 00:38:29,471
          <i> MARY JAYNE</i>           
      <i> WAS MORAN'S WIFE.</i>        

876
00:38:29,539 --> 00:38:33,241
 <i> IT'S THESE PERSONAL DETAILS</i>   
 <i> IN THE DIARY THAT HAUNT JIM.</i>  

877
00:38:33,310 --> 00:38:35,610
                   "MAY 9, 1944.

878
00:38:35,679 --> 00:38:37,846
              "AN AIRMAIL LETTER
              FROM MY ANGEL.    

879
00:38:37,914 --> 00:38:40,782
         "MY BABY IS PRETTY SURE
         SHE IS PREGNANT.       

880
00:38:40,851 --> 00:38:43,051
                     "THANK GOD!

881
00:38:43,120 --> 00:38:45,320
      "BOUGHT THE BOYS BEER     
      WITH MY LAST SIX SHILLINGS

882
00:38:45,389 --> 00:38:46,755
                  TO CELEBRATE."

883
00:38:46,823 --> 00:38:48,957
THAT'S REALLY GREAT.            

884
00:38:49,025 --> 00:38:51,893
 <i> THERE'S SOMETHING IMPORTANT</i>   
   <i> MISSING FROM THIS DIARY:</i>    

885
00:38:51,962 --> 00:38:53,495
          <i> AN ENDING.</i>           

886
00:38:53,563 --> 00:38:56,431
      <i> THE LAST ENTRY IS</i>        
      <i> FROM OCTOBER 29th,</i>       

887
00:38:56,500 --> 00:38:59,267
 <i> SEVEN MONTHS BEFORE THE END</i>   
    <i> OF THE WAR IN EUROPE.</i>      

888
00:38:59,336 --> 00:39:00,802
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?          

889
00:39:00,871 --> 00:39:04,272
 WELL, WES, I'D LIKE TO FIND OUT
 WHAT HAPPENED TO BILL MORAN,   

890
00:39:04,341 --> 00:39:08,009
            IF HE CAME BACK HOME
            OR IF HE WAS KILLED.

891
00:39:08,078 --> 00:39:10,411
         I'D LIKE TO REALLY KNOW
         WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM.  

892
00:39:10,480 --> 00:39:12,881
         <i> JIM IS EAGER</i>          
      <i> TO KNOW MORE ABOUT</i>       

893
00:39:12,949 --> 00:39:15,984
 <i> WHAT THE MEN HIS FATHER FLEW</i>  
       <i> WITH SAW AND DID</i>        

894
00:39:16,052 --> 00:39:17,852
      <i> DURING THEIR TIME</i>        
         <i> IN ENGLAND.</i>           

895
00:39:17,921 --> 00:39:20,355
      <i> AND HE WANTS HELP</i>        
 <i> WITH ANOTHER QUESTION, TOO.</i>   

896
00:39:20,423 --> 00:39:22,891
         I WOULD LIKE TO BE ABLE
         TO REUNITE THE DIARY   

897
00:39:22,959 --> 00:39:25,026
       WITH BILL MORAN'S FAMILY.

898
00:39:25,095 --> 00:39:28,596
    I THINK IT'S VERY IMPORTANT 
    FOR THE FAMILY TO HAVE THIS.

899
00:39:28,665 --> 00:39:31,099
I'M GOING TO HAVE TO TAKE       
THE DIARY WITH ME,              

900
00:39:31,168 --> 00:39:33,668
AND I'M READY TO GET GOING.     

901
00:39:33,737 --> 00:39:36,237
       WELL, LET'S SEE.         

902
00:39:36,306 --> 00:39:38,473
     EVERY TIME I READ ONE      
  OF THESE SOLDIER'S DIARIES,   

903
00:39:38,542 --> 00:39:40,208
     I JUST GET THE SENSE       

904
00:39:40,277 --> 00:39:43,578
   THAT I'M HOLDING A PIECE     
    OF HISTORY IN MY HAND.      

905
00:39:43,647 --> 00:39:45,747
       <i> THE DIARY COVERS</i>        
        <i> ABOUT A YEAR,</i>          

906
00:39:45,816 --> 00:39:50,451
      <i> FROM OCTOBER 1943</i>        
       <i> TO OCTOBER 1944.</i>        

907
00:39:50,520 --> 00:39:52,387
          <i> MUCH OF IT</i>           
   <i> IS WRITTEN MECHANICALLY,</i>    

908
00:39:52,455 --> 00:39:55,323
       <i> MORE LIKE A LOG</i>         
   <i> THAN A PERSONAL JOURNAL.</i>    

909
00:39:55,392 --> 00:39:58,459
  <i> BUT IT'S CLEAR HIS UNIT IS</i>   
 <i> IN THE THICK OF THE ACTION.</i>   

910
00:39:58,528 --> 00:40:01,162
          HERE'S ONE,           
        SEPTEMBER 27th.         

911
00:40:01,231 --> 00:40:02,830
       "STARTED A LETTER        
         TO MY ANGEL,           

912
00:40:02,899 --> 00:40:05,433
     "BUT BAHN STOPPED IN       
          TO TELL ME            

913
00:40:05,502 --> 00:40:07,769
        "OUR SQUAD LOST         
       FOUR OUT OF NINE.        

914
00:40:07,837 --> 00:40:10,271
  IT WAS WITHEY'S LAST ONE."    

915
00:40:10,340 --> 00:40:13,308
  <i> A LOT OF BOMBERS WENT DOWN</i>   
     <i> WITH MEN MORAN KNEW.</i>      

916
00:40:13,376 --> 00:40:15,743
   <i> IF HE'S SHAKEN BY THIS,</i>     
      <i> I WOULDN'T KNOW IT</i>       

917
00:40:15,812 --> 00:40:18,146
   <i> FROM THE MATTER-OF-FACT</i>     
          <i> LANGUAGE.</i>            

918
00:40:18,215 --> 00:40:20,782
   <i> AND HERE'S BILL MORAN'S</i>     
         <i> LAST ENTRY,</i>           

919
00:40:20,850 --> 00:40:23,851
      <i> OCTOBER 29, 1944.</i>        

920
00:40:23,920 --> 00:40:27,689
     <i> MORE DEATH AND MORE</i>       
   <i> MATTER-OF-FACT LANGUAGE.</i>    

921
00:40:27,757 --> 00:40:30,258
         BILL WRITES,           
     "MASS AND COMMUNION.       

922
00:40:30,327 --> 00:40:32,160
      "PUT A COUPLE HOURS       
          ON A SHIP.            

923
00:40:32,229 --> 00:40:34,929
"HEARD A ROTTEN GERMAN BROADCAST
        LATE LAST NIGHT         

924
00:40:34,998 --> 00:40:37,298
      CALLING EISENHOWER        
            A RAT."             

925
00:40:37,367 --> 00:40:40,501
    <i> BUT THERE ARE NO CLUES</i>     
  <i> WHY MORAN STOPPED WRITING.</i>   

926
00:40:40,570 --> 00:40:44,372
  <i> DID HE GO BACK HOME OR WAS</i>   
   <i> HIS NEXT MISSION FATAL?</i>     

927
00:40:46,876 --> 00:40:48,776
       <i> THERE ARE PLENTY</i>        
        <i> OF NAMES HERE.</i>         

928
00:40:48,845 --> 00:40:51,746
   <i> MAYBE SOMEONE BILL MORAN</i>    
  <i> WROTE ABOUT IS STILL ALIVE</i>   

929
00:40:51,815 --> 00:40:55,383
       <i> AND CAN FILL IN</i>         
  <i> THESE BLANK PAGES FOR ME.</i>    

930
00:40:55,452 --> 00:40:59,053
    "LENNY," IT LOOKS LIKE.     

931
00:40:59,122 --> 00:41:01,155
           "GOLDEN."            

932
00:41:01,224 --> 00:41:06,694
    "CHAPPY, PELTON, AND I      
    WERE LUCKY NOT TO GO."      

933
00:41:06,763 --> 00:41:10,031
 <i> I'LL CALL MY OFFICE AND ASK</i>   
  <i> THEM TO TRY TO TRACK DOWN</i>    

934
00:41:10,100 --> 00:41:12,734
     <i> SOME OF BILL MORAN'S</i>      
         <i> WAR BUDDIES.</i>          

935
00:41:12,802 --> 00:41:14,302
                      WES COWAN.
    BILL OLDSON.                

936
00:41:14,371 --> 00:41:15,837
GLAD TO MEET YOU, WES.          

937
00:41:15,905 --> 00:41:17,639
   <i> WHILE THEY'RE SEARCHING,</i>    
     <i> I'VE COME TO FLORIDA</i>      

938
00:41:17,707 --> 00:41:19,507
    <i> TO MEET WITH PROFESSOR</i>     
        <i> WILLIAM OLDSON</i>         

939
00:41:19,576 --> 00:41:21,576
      <i> FROM THE INSTITUTE</i>       
       <i> ON WORLD WAR II</i>         

940
00:41:21,645 --> 00:41:23,344
  <i> AND THE HUMAN EXPERIENCE.</i>    

941
00:41:23,413 --> 00:41:26,014
HERE'S THE DIARY THAT I SENT YOU
THE TRANSCRIPT OF.              

942
00:41:26,082 --> 00:41:27,915
                       OH, NICE.

943
00:41:27,984 --> 00:41:29,450
             VERY UNUSUAL COVER.

944
00:41:29,519 --> 00:41:31,152
              AND IF I MUST SAY,

945
00:41:31,221 --> 00:41:33,688
          HIS HANDWRITING'S     
          BETTER THAN MOST, TOO.

946
00:41:33,757 --> 00:41:36,257
   <i> WILLIAM SAYS UNEARTHING</i>     
<i> JOURNALS FROM THE BATTLEFRONT</i>  

947
00:41:36,326 --> 00:41:38,726
          <i> IS ALWAYS</i>            
   <i> AN IMPORTANT DISCOVERY,</i>     

948
00:41:38,795 --> 00:41:42,563
  <i> A UNIQUE WINDOW ON THE MEN</i>   
<i> WHO ACTUALLY DID THE FIGHTING.</i> 

949
00:41:42,632 --> 00:41:44,198
     IT'S THE UNVARNISHED TRUTH,

950
00:41:44,267 --> 00:41:46,768
  AND IT'S THE YARDSTICK YOU CAN
  HOLD UP TO EVERYTHING ELSE -- 

951
00:41:46,836 --> 00:41:48,903
            TO THE LETTERS HOME,
            TO THE PROPAGANDA,  

952
00:41:48,972 --> 00:41:50,304
              TO THE NEWSREEL --

953
00:41:50,373 --> 00:41:52,140
                AND SAY, "HERE'S
                WHAT HE FELT."  

954
00:41:52,208 --> 00:41:54,809
   <i> AND THERE CERTAINLY WAS</i>     
    <i> A LOT TO WRITE ABOUT.</i>      

955
00:41:54,878 --> 00:41:58,046
    <i> WILLIAM EXPLAINS THAT</i>      
           <i> IN 1943,</i>            

956
00:41:58,114 --> 00:42:01,349
<i> ALLIED BOMBING RAIDS ON GERMANY</i>
    <i> ARE OFTEN INEFFECTUAL</i>      

957
00:42:01,418 --> 00:42:04,452
     <i> AT HITTING MILITARY</i>       
   <i> AND INDUSTRIAL TARGETS.</i>     

958
00:42:04,521 --> 00:42:09,724
<i> BUT BY 1944, WITH FORD CRANKING</i>
  <i> OUT A NEW B-24 EVERY HOUR,</i>   

959
00:42:09,793 --> 00:42:12,693
     <i> THE AMERICAN BOMBERS</i>      
  <i> ARE SUCCESSFULLY TARGETING</i>   

960
00:42:12,762 --> 00:42:15,096
      <i> HITLER'S FACTORIES</i>       
      <i> AND FUEL SUPPLIES</i>        

961
00:42:15,165 --> 00:42:18,099
   <i> AND HELPING TURN THE WAR</i>    
    <i> IN THE ALLIES' FAVOR.</i>      

962
00:42:18,168 --> 00:42:21,469
    <i> BUT THE CARNAGE AMONG</i>      
 <i> FLIGHT CREWS IS HORRENDOUS.</i>   

963
00:42:21,538 --> 00:42:24,238
              IN '43, WE LOST   
              OVER 3,000 PLANES.

964
00:42:24,307 --> 00:42:26,974
             '44, WE LOSE       
             OVER 11,000 PLANES.

965
00:42:27,043 --> 00:42:28,843
       <i> WILLIAM BELIEVES</i>        
    <i> THERE'S A GOOD CHANCE</i>      

966
00:42:28,912 --> 00:42:31,145
       <i> MORAN WAS KILLED</i>        
        <i> OVER GERMANY.</i>          

967
00:42:31,214 --> 00:42:34,282
    <i> FLYING DAYLIGHT RAIDS</i>      
  <i> MADE THE BOMBERS EASY PREY</i>   

968
00:42:34,350 --> 00:42:37,218
  <i> FOR GERMAN FIGHTER PLANES</i>    
   <i> AND ANTI-AIRCRAFT GUNS.</i>     

969
00:42:37,287 --> 00:42:39,153
    IF YOU WERE FLYING          
    WITH BRITISH BOMBER COMMAND,

970
00:42:39,222 --> 00:42:42,023
            YOU HAD A 65% CHANCE
            OF BEING A CASUALTY.

971
00:42:42,091 --> 00:42:44,525
     IF YOU'RE FLYING IN        
     THE AMERICAN 8th AIR FORCE,

972
00:42:44,594 --> 00:42:47,495
  YOU'VE GOT A 40% TO 60% CHANCE
  OF BEING A CASUALTY.          

973
00:42:47,564 --> 00:42:50,064
    IF YOU'RE LUCKY ENOUGH TO BE
    IN THAT KAMIKAZE SQUADRON,  

974
00:42:50,133 --> 00:42:53,167
    YOU'VE ONLY GOT A 53% CHANCE
    OF BEING A CASUALTY.        

975
00:42:53,236 --> 00:42:54,802
YOU'RE KIDDING ME.              

976
00:42:54,871 --> 00:42:56,370
   <i> WHILE LOGISTICS PROBLEMS</i>    

977
00:42:56,439 --> 00:42:59,473
 <i> OFTEN KEPT JAPANESE KAMIKAZE</i>  
     <i> SQUADRONS GROUNDED,</i>       

978
00:42:59,542 --> 00:43:01,943
          <i> IN EUROPE,</i>           
    <i> THE BIG ALLIED BOMBERS</i>     

979
00:43:02,011 --> 00:43:04,378
      <i> WERE SEEING COMBAT</i>       
        <i> ALMOST DAILY.</i>          

980
00:43:04,447 --> 00:43:08,349
SO A KAMIKAZE PILOT             
WHO'S SUPPOSED TO KILL HIMSELF  

981
00:43:08,418 --> 00:43:11,152
STOOD A BETTER CHANCE           
OF SURVIVING                    

982
00:43:11,221 --> 00:43:13,621
THAN A B-24 BOMBER PILOT?       

983
00:43:13,690 --> 00:43:15,223
                HARD TO BELIEVE,
                ISN'T IT?       

984
00:43:15,291 --> 00:43:18,259
<i> WILLIAM SAYS THE OFTEN REMOTE,</i> 
   <i> MATTER-OF-FACT LANGUAGE</i>     

985
00:43:18,328 --> 00:43:20,027
   <i> IN SUCH WARTIME WRITING</i>     

986
00:43:20,096 --> 00:43:22,430
   <i> WAS A WAY OF WALLING OFF</i>    
         <i> OR ESCAPING</i>           

987
00:43:22,498 --> 00:43:24,498
          <i> THE HORROR</i>           
      <i> OF EVERYDAY LIFE.</i>        

988
00:43:24,567 --> 00:43:26,634
  I THINK IT'S NOT ONLY TYPICAL,
  IT'S NECESSARY.               

989
00:43:26,703 --> 00:43:28,169
                THEY CAN'T BROOD
                ABOUT IT.       

990
00:43:28,238 --> 00:43:30,538
     IT'S GOING TO INTERFERE    
     WITH THEIR OWN PERFORMANCE,

991
00:43:30,607 --> 00:43:32,440
     IT'S GOING TO DEPRESS THEM.

992
00:43:32,508 --> 00:43:35,042
    <i> THE WRITING IS A FORM</i>      
       <i> OF SELF-DEFENSE.</i>        

993
00:43:35,111 --> 00:43:36,978
        WHAT'S UNUSUAL          
        ABOUT THE DIARY YOU HAVE

994
00:43:37,046 --> 00:43:39,513
          IS THE ROMANTIC ASPECT
          OF IT.                

995
00:43:39,582 --> 00:43:41,649
    I DON'T KNOW ANY OTHER DIARY
    THAT I'VE SEEN              

996
00:43:41,718 --> 00:43:45,019
      WHERE SOMEBODY'S REFERRING
      TO HIS WIFE AS "ANGEL."   

997
00:43:45,088 --> 00:43:47,822
  AND WE HAVE LOTS OF LETTERS   
  WHERE IT SAYS, "HELLO, HONEY,"

998
00:43:47,890 --> 00:43:50,491
      OR SOMETHING OF THAT SORT,
      BUT NOT IN THE DIARIES.   

999
00:43:50,560 --> 00:43:52,727
THANKS VERY MUCH                
FOR SHARING THIS WITH ME.       

1000
00:43:52,795 --> 00:43:54,161
        THANK YOU FOR LETTING ME
        SEE THIS.               

1001
00:43:54,230 --> 00:43:55,997
          THIS IS A VERY SPECIAL
          DOCUMENT.             

1002
00:43:56,065 --> 00:43:57,898
      <i> I STILL DON'T KNOW</i>       
         <i> EXACTLY WHY</i>           

1003
00:43:57,967 --> 00:44:00,268
  <i> BILL MORAN STOPPED WRITING</i>   
       <i> IN THE JOURNAL,</i>         

1004
00:44:00,336 --> 00:44:02,236
        <i> BUT MY OFFICE</i>          
        <i> HAS BEEN ABLE</i>          

1005
00:44:02,305 --> 00:44:04,505
        <i> TO TRACK DOWN</i>          
    <i> HIS MILITARY RECORDS,</i>      

1006
00:44:04,574 --> 00:44:06,674
    <i> AND THEY'VE SENT THEM</i>      
    <i> TO ME AT THE LIBRARY.</i>      

1007
00:44:09,512 --> 00:44:11,145
     <i> IT'S SOBERING NEWS.</i>       

1008
00:44:11,214 --> 00:44:14,215
     <i> ON OCTOBER 31, 1944,</i>      

1009
00:44:14,284 --> 00:44:17,051
    <i> BILL MORAN WAS FLYING</i>      
   <i> WITH PILOT EDWARD SPEERS</i>    

1010
00:44:17,120 --> 00:44:19,687
      <i> AND SIX OTHER MEN</i>        
<i> WHEN THEIR PLANE DISAPPEARED.</i>  

1011
00:44:19,756 --> 00:44:23,024
          THIS REPORT           
     OF AIRCRAFT ACCIDENT       

1012
00:44:23,092 --> 00:44:27,495
  OR MISSING AIRCRAFT REPORT    
CONFIRMS THAT MORAN WAS KILLED  

1013
00:44:27,563 --> 00:44:29,830
        IN SOME SORT OF         
     A TRAINING ACCIDENT.       

1014
00:44:29,899 --> 00:44:32,333
   THEY'RE NOT CLEAR EXACTLY    
        WHAT HAPPENED.          

1015
00:44:32,402 --> 00:44:33,834
          HE TOOK OFF           
       IN THE FORMATION.        

1016
00:44:33,903 --> 00:44:35,369
      AFTER HE TOOK OFF,        

1017
00:44:35,438 --> 00:44:38,239
  NOBODY ELSE IN THE AIRCRAFT   
 FORMATION EVER SAW HIM AGAIN.  

1018
00:44:38,307 --> 00:44:41,842
<i> THE WRECKAGE AND MORAN'S BODY</i>  
       <i> ARE NEVER FOUND.</i>        

1019
00:44:41,911 --> 00:44:46,747
THIS TOOK PLACE TWO DAYS AFTER  
 THE LAST ENTRY IN HIS DIARY.   

1020
00:44:46,816 --> 00:44:50,951
 <i> MARY JAYNE WAS SEVEN MONTHS</i>   
   <i> PREGNANT WHEN BILL DIED.</i>    

1021
00:44:51,020 --> 00:44:53,988
<i> IF I'M GOING TO HELP JIM RETURN</i>
<i> THE JOURNAL TO BILL'S FAMILY,</i>  

1022
00:44:54,057 --> 00:44:57,024
    <i> I'M GOING TO NEED HELP</i>     
<i> TRACKING DOWN HIS DESCENDANTS.</i> 

1023
00:44:57,093 --> 00:44:59,593
    <i> MY OFFICE HAS LOCATED</i>      
         <i> JACK PELTON,</i>          

1024
00:44:59,662 --> 00:45:02,229
    <i> ONE OF MORAN'S BUDDIES</i>     
   <i> MENTIONED IN THE DIARY.</i>     

1025
00:45:02,298 --> 00:45:03,364
HEY, JACK.                      

1026
00:45:03,433 --> 00:45:04,565
                   HEY, WES.    

1027
00:45:04,634 --> 00:45:06,033
    <i> JACK AGREES TO MEET ME</i>     

1028
00:45:06,102 --> 00:45:08,602
<i> AT THE AMERICAN AERO SERVICES</i>  
      <i> HANGAR IN FLORIDA,</i>       

1029
00:45:08,671 --> 00:45:12,840
<i> WHERE THE COLLINGS FOUNDATION</i>  
   <i> MAINTAINS A B-24 BOMBER.</i>    

1030
00:45:12,909 --> 00:45:14,642
BOY, THIS IS QUITE A PIECE      
OF MACHINERY, ISN'T IT?         

1031
00:45:14,710 --> 00:45:16,977
      OH, IT REALLY IS,         
      IT'S A WONDERFUL AIRPLANE.

1032
00:45:17,046 --> 00:45:18,712
AND YOU WERE A PILOT            
OF ONE OF THESE BIRDS.          

1033
00:45:18,781 --> 00:45:20,214
               I WAS A PILOT,   
               FLEW 32 MISSIONS.

1034
00:45:20,283 --> 00:45:21,582
HOW'D YOU LIKE TO GET UP        
IN THE COCKPIT?                 

1035
00:45:21,651 --> 00:45:22,650
           LOVE TO.             

1036
00:45:22,718 --> 00:45:23,984
        OH, WONDERFUL.          

1037
00:45:24,053 --> 00:45:25,653
 <i> IT'S BEEN MORE THAN 50 YEARS</i>  

1038
00:45:25,721 --> 00:45:28,022
  <i> SINCE JACK'S TAKEN A SEAT</i>    
       <i> AT THE CONTROLS.</i>        

1039
00:45:28,091 --> 00:45:30,791
SO WHAT WAS IT LIKE             
TO FLY ONE OF THESE BABIES?     

1040
00:45:30,860 --> 00:45:32,560
           IT WAS VERY EXCITING,
           REALLY.              

1041
00:45:32,628 --> 00:45:34,395
        <i> JACK TELLS ME</i>          
      <i> IN ORDER TO ATTACK</i>       

1042
00:45:34,464 --> 00:45:36,197
  <i> HEAVILY DEFENDED TARGETS,</i>    

1043
00:45:36,265 --> 00:45:38,065
        <i> PILOTS LIKE HE</i>         
     <i> AND BILL MORAN FLEW</i>       

1044
00:45:38,134 --> 00:45:40,801
         <i> AT ALTITUDES</i>          
      <i> OVER 20,000 FEET,</i>        

1045
00:45:40,870 --> 00:45:44,438
  <i> WHERE TEMPERATURES REACHED</i>   
      <i> MINUS 30 DEGREES.</i>        

1046
00:45:44,507 --> 00:45:46,907
  SO IT WAS COLD,               
  YOU'RE WEARING AN OXYGEN MASK.

1047
00:45:46,976 --> 00:45:49,443
       THERE ARE NO HYDRAULICS  
       IN THESE STEERING WHEELS.

1048
00:45:49,512 --> 00:45:52,813
               IT MUST HAVE BEEN
               A HELL OF A JOB. 

1049
00:45:52,882 --> 00:45:55,216
       IT WAS A STRANGE FEELING.

1050
00:45:55,284 --> 00:45:56,984
               YOU WERE         
               IN ANOTHER WORLD.

1051
00:45:57,053 --> 00:45:59,086
      <i> JACK EXPLAINS THAT</i>       
    <i> THE LIGHTWEIGHT FRAME</i>      

1052
00:45:59,155 --> 00:46:01,922
      <i> THAT MADE THE B-24</i>       
   <i> SUCH AN EFFICIENT BOMBER</i>    

1053
00:46:01,991 --> 00:46:04,792
   <i> ALSO MADE IT VULNERABLE</i>     
        <i> TO ENEMY FIRE.</i>         

1054
00:46:04,861 --> 00:46:07,495
   WE BROUGHT ONE PLANE HOME    
     WITH 153 HOLES IN IT.      

1055
00:46:07,563 --> 00:46:09,296
    [ machine gun firing ]      

1056
00:46:09,365 --> 00:46:11,565
      <i> BULLETS AND SHELLS</i>       
  <i> FROM GERMAN FIGHTER PLANES</i>   

1057
00:46:11,634 --> 00:46:13,801
         <i> TORE THROUGH</i>          
    <i> THE AMERICAN AIRCRAFT</i>      

1058
00:46:13,870 --> 00:46:16,537
   <i> AND HELPED EARN THE B-24</i>    
        <i> ITS REPUTATION</i>         

1059
00:46:16,606 --> 00:46:19,073
     <i> AS A FLYING COFFIN.</i>       

1060
00:46:19,141 --> 00:46:22,476
        YOU KNOW, I'VE GOT      
        BILL MORAN'S DIARY HERE.

1061
00:46:22,545 --> 00:46:24,245
              WHAT KIND OF A GUY
              WAS BILL MORAN?   

1062
00:46:24,313 --> 00:46:25,646
WHAT WAS HE LIKE?               

1063
00:46:25,715 --> 00:46:27,348
               BILL MORAN WAS   
               A GREAT CO-PILOT,

1064
00:46:27,416 --> 00:46:30,084
           GREAT SENSE OF HUMOR,
           IRISHMAN ALL THE WAY.

1065
00:46:30,152 --> 00:46:32,753
      <i> JACK HAS A PICTURE</i>       
   <i> OF BILL AND MARY JAYNE,</i>     

1066
00:46:32,822 --> 00:46:34,388
    <i> BILL'S PREGNANT WIFE,</i>      

1067
00:46:34,457 --> 00:46:37,124
      <i> TAKEN RIGHT BEFORE</i>       
 <i> THE AIRMAN LEFT THE STATES.</i>   

1068
00:46:37,193 --> 00:46:39,526
                 SO THAT'S BILL.
    BILL.                       

1069
00:46:39,595 --> 00:46:40,895
              THAT'S MARY JAYNE.

1070
00:46:40,963 --> 00:46:43,063
            AND LOOK AT THEM    
            HOLDING HANDS THERE.

1071
00:46:43,132 --> 00:46:45,199
               I'D RECOGNIZE YOU
               ANYWHERE.        

1072
00:46:45,268 --> 00:46:46,901
        IT LOOKS LIKE YOU GUYS  
        ARE HAVING A LOT OF FUN.

1073
00:46:46,969 --> 00:46:48,836
YEAH, WE DID,                   
HAD A GREAT EVENING.            

1074
00:46:48,905 --> 00:46:51,605
LAST TIME WE SAW OUR WIVES      
FOR A YEAR.                     

1075
00:46:51,674 --> 00:46:55,175
      ONE MORE QUESTION:        
      WHERE WAS BILL MORAN FROM?

1076
00:46:55,244 --> 00:46:56,944
PITTSBURGH, PENNSYLVANIA.       

1077
00:46:57,013 --> 00:46:58,579
MARY JAYNE WAS FROM THERE,      
TOO, THEN?                      

1078
00:46:58,648 --> 00:46:59,847
                   YES, SHE WAS.

1079
00:46:59,916 --> 00:47:01,482
WHAT EVER HAPPENED TO           
MARY JAYNE, DO YOU KNOW?        

1080
00:47:01,550 --> 00:47:02,950
                   I DON'T KNOW.

1081
00:47:03,019 --> 00:47:04,885
  I TRIED TO FIND HER           
  WHEN I GOT BACK IN THE STATES,

1082
00:47:04,954 --> 00:47:06,186
                      COULD NOT.

1083
00:47:06,255 --> 00:47:08,255
      ONE TIME WHEN I WAS       
      ON BUSINESS IN PITTSBURGH,

1084
00:47:08,324 --> 00:47:10,124
          I HEARD SHE WAS THERE,

1085
00:47:10,192 --> 00:47:12,760
            BUT I STILL COULDN'T
            TRACK HER DOWN.     

1086
00:47:12,828 --> 00:47:14,261
         <i> SO I'M BACK</i>           
        <i> AT THE LIBRARY</i>         

1087
00:47:14,330 --> 00:47:17,097
      <i> TO SEARCH THROUGH</i>        
    <i> GENEALOGICAL RECORDS.</i>      

1088
00:47:17,166 --> 00:47:22,102
   <i> AT FIRST, I DRAW A BLANK</i>    
   <i> LOOKING FOR MARY JAYNE.</i>     

1089
00:47:22,171 --> 00:47:25,472
 <i> MAYBE I CAN GET INFORMATION</i>   
 <i> FROM ANOTHER FAMILY MEMBER.</i>   

1090
00:47:25,541 --> 00:47:26,907
    <i> I FINALLY GET A BREAK</i>      

1091
00:47:26,976 --> 00:47:28,709
   <i> WITH THE SOCIAL SECURITY</i>    
         <i> DEATH INDEX</i>           

1092
00:47:28,778 --> 00:47:30,544
 <i> FOR BILL'S MOTHER VERONICA.</i>   

1093
00:47:30,613 --> 00:47:32,212
      BINGO, HERE SHE IS.       

1094
00:47:32,281 --> 00:47:38,385
    SHE DIED IN MARCH 1967      
      IN MIAMI, FLORIDA.        

1095
00:47:38,454 --> 00:47:40,454
         <i> HER OBITUARY</i>          
     <i> EVENTUALLY LEADS US</i>       

1096
00:47:40,523 --> 00:47:43,223
     <i> TO THE NAMES OF TWO</i>       
 <i> OF BILL'S SURVIVING SISTERS:</i>  

1097
00:47:43,292 --> 00:47:45,693
        <i> ADELAIDE YOUNG</i>         
      <i> AND JEANIE KIMBROW</i>       

1098
00:47:45,761 --> 00:47:48,062
     <i> OF SEBRING, FLORIDA.</i>      

1099
00:47:48,130 --> 00:47:52,232
 <i> IF THERE'S A LOCAL LISTING,</i>   
   <i> MAYBE WE'RE IN BUSINESS.</i>    

1100
00:47:52,301 --> 00:47:55,636
      <i> IT TAKES A WHILE,</i>        
 <i> BUT EVENTUALLY I GET LUCKY.</i>   

1101
00:47:55,705 --> 00:47:57,604
        ADELAIDE YOUNG,         
   THERE'S HER PHONE NUMBER,    

1102
00:47:57,673 --> 00:48:00,674
           ADDRESS,             
       BORN AUGUST 1930.        

1103
00:48:00,743 --> 00:48:02,042
      IT'S GOT TO BE HER.       

1104
00:48:02,111 --> 00:48:04,211
  I CAN'T BELIEVE I'VE FOUND    
      A LIVING RELATIVE.        

1105
00:48:04,280 --> 00:48:05,746
      HELLO, MRS. YOUNG?        

1106
00:48:05,815 --> 00:48:08,282
     <i> ADELAIDE IS EXCITED</i>       
    <i> BY NEWS OF THE DIARY,</i>      

1107
00:48:08,350 --> 00:48:10,384
      <i> AND WE MAKE PLANS</i>        
           <i> TO MEET.</i>            

1108
00:48:10,453 --> 00:48:11,885
YOU KNOW WHY                    
I'VE COME TO SEE YOU.           

1109
00:48:11,954 --> 00:48:13,420
                    YES.        

1110
00:48:13,489 --> 00:48:18,492
I HAVE A DIARY THAT WAS WRITTEN 
BY YOUR BROTHER.                

1111
00:48:18,561 --> 00:48:23,530
                OH, "MY LIFE    
                IN THE SERVICE."

1112
00:48:23,599 --> 00:48:25,332
DO YOU RECOGNIZE                
THAT HANDWRITING?               

1113
00:48:25,401 --> 00:48:27,634
                  OH, OF COURSE.

1114
00:48:27,703 --> 00:48:29,970
 <i> IT'S THE CONSTANT REFERENCES</i>  
        <i> TO BILL'S WIFE</i>         

1115
00:48:30,039 --> 00:48:31,872
  <i> THAT CATCH ADELAIDE'S EYE.</i>   

1116
00:48:31,941 --> 00:48:36,410
         HE ALWAYS SPEAKS OF HER
         IN SUCH A GENTLE WAY.  

1117
00:48:36,479 --> 00:48:38,912
YOU GET THE SENSE THAT          
THEY WERE REALLY IN LOVE.       

1118
00:48:38,981 --> 00:48:42,349
               OH, FROM THE TIME
               THEY MET.        

1119
00:48:42,418 --> 00:48:45,853
       <i> ADELAIDE WAS 14</i>         
    <i> WHEN HER BROTHER DIED.</i>     

1120
00:48:45,921 --> 00:48:48,422
       THE TELEGRAM WAS LAYING  
       ON THE DINING ROOM TABLE,

1121
00:48:48,491 --> 00:48:51,458
    AND WE KEPT SAYING, "THEY'LL
    FIND HIM, THEY'LL FIND HIM. 

1122
00:48:51,527 --> 00:48:53,861
      SOMEDAY THEY'LL FIND HIM."

1123
00:48:53,929 --> 00:48:56,663
    THERE WAS NEVER ANY         
    MEMORIAL SERVICE OR ANYTHING

1124
00:48:56,732 --> 00:48:58,932
              BECAUSE "SOMEDAY  
              THEY'LL FIND HIM."

1125
00:48:59,001 --> 00:49:01,502
  <i> AT FIRST THE VERY PREGNANT</i>   
          <i> MARY JAYNE</i>           

1126
00:49:01,570 --> 00:49:04,071
       <i> WASN'T EVEN TOLD</i>        
   <i> HER HUSBAND WAS MISSING.</i>    

1127
00:49:04,140 --> 00:49:06,173
       <i> SHE LEARNED BILL</i>        
       <i> HAD BEEN KILLED</i>         

1128
00:49:06,242 --> 00:49:07,875
        <i> FROM A FRIEND</i>          
       <i> WHO VISITED HER</i>         

1129
00:49:07,943 --> 00:49:10,744
<i> RIGHT AFTER SHE'D GIVEN BIRTH</i>  
      <i> TO THEIR DAUGHTER.</i>       

1130
00:49:10,813 --> 00:49:12,880
           SHE WAS INCONSOLABLE.

1131
00:49:12,948 --> 00:49:17,117
          SHE WAS JUST          
          UNBELIEVABLY IN GRIEF.

1132
00:49:17,186 --> 00:49:20,587
   <i> MARY JAYNE DIED ROUGHLY</i>     
 <i> 20 YEARS AFTER HER HUSBAND,</i>   

1133
00:49:20,656 --> 00:49:22,656
      <i> BUT WHAT ADELAIDE</i>        
        <i> REVEALED NEXT</i>          

1134
00:49:22,725 --> 00:49:25,125
  <i> WILL BE EXTRAORDINARY NEWS</i>   
           <i> FOR JIM.</i>            

1135
00:49:25,194 --> 00:49:27,761
     THIS HAS BEEN              
     AN INCREDIBLE STORY FOR ME.

1136
00:49:27,830 --> 00:49:30,164
   <i> I TELL JIM ABOUT SOME OF</i>    
   <i> THE THINGS I'VE LEARNED</i>     

1137
00:49:30,232 --> 00:49:32,132
        <i> WHILE WORKING</i>          
       <i> ON BILL'S DIARY.</i>        

1138
00:49:32,201 --> 00:49:34,535
   I'VE GOT TO TELL YOU, THOUGH,
   THAT I HAVE SOME BAD NEWS.   

1139
00:49:34,603 --> 00:49:37,604
<i> I LET JIM KNOW THAT BILL MORAN</i> 
  <i> DIED IN A TRAINING MISSION</i>   

1140
00:49:37,673 --> 00:49:40,807
   <i> AND HIS WIFE PASSED AWAY</i>    
      <i> OVER 40 YEARS AGO,</i>       

1141
00:49:40,876 --> 00:49:43,176
        <i> BUT THE STORY</i>          
      <i> DOESN'T END THERE.</i>       

1142
00:49:43,245 --> 00:49:45,345
            THERE'S SOMEONE I DO
            WANT YOU TO MEET,   

1143
00:49:45,414 --> 00:49:48,849
    SO IF YOU WANT TO FOLLOW ME,
    WE'LL GO MEET THAT PERSON.  

1144
00:49:48,918 --> 00:49:50,517
I'D LIKE TO DO THAT.            

1145
00:49:50,586 --> 00:49:52,686
       <i> ADELAIDE TOLD ME</i>        
        <i> THAT THE BABY</i>          

1146
00:49:52,755 --> 00:49:55,022
        <i> THAT BILL WAS</i>          
     <i> SO EAGERLY EXPECTING</i>      

1147
00:49:55,090 --> 00:49:58,191
       <i> WAS BORN 32 DAYS</i>        
        <i> AFTER HE DIED.</i>         

1148
00:49:58,260 --> 00:49:59,760
     <i> HER NAME WAS JANIE.</i>       

1149
00:49:59,828 --> 00:50:01,194
                  SHE'S MARRIED.

1150
00:50:01,263 --> 00:50:04,131
         SHE HAS TWO CHILDREN   
         AND FOUR GRANDCHILDREN.

1151
00:50:04,199 --> 00:50:08,268
  <i> BILL MORAN WOULD HAVE BEEN</i>   
     <i> A GREAT-GRANDFATHER.</i>      

1152
00:50:08,337 --> 00:50:09,436
HEY, GUYS.                      

1153
00:50:09,505 --> 00:50:10,637
                          HI.   

1154
00:50:10,706 --> 00:50:12,706
I WANT YOU TO MEET SOMEBODY,    
JIM.                            

1155
00:50:12,775 --> 00:50:14,241
THIS IS JIM CHAPMAN.            

1156
00:50:14,310 --> 00:50:15,776
THIS IS CHAPPY'S SON.           

1157
00:50:15,844 --> 00:50:18,011
                HI, HOW ARE YOU?

1158
00:50:18,080 --> 00:50:19,780
THIS IS ADELAIDE YOUNG.         

1159
00:50:19,848 --> 00:50:21,548
THIS IS BILL'S SISTER.          

1160
00:50:21,617 --> 00:50:23,050
              I REMEMBER HIM    
              TALKING ABOUT --  

1161
00:50:23,118 --> 00:50:24,418
OH, HI, ADELAIDE.               

1162
00:50:24,486 --> 00:50:26,887
    HE TALKED ABOUT BILL CHAPMAN
    ALL THE TIME.               

1163
00:50:26,956 --> 00:50:28,755
OH, IT'S SO NICE                
TO MEET YOU.                    

1164
00:50:28,824 --> 00:50:30,924
                 OH, I'M SO GLAD
                 TO MEET YOU.   

1165
00:50:30,993 --> 00:50:35,028
    AND THIS IS BILL'S DAUGHTER,
    JANIE.                      

1166
00:50:35,097 --> 00:50:37,898
          HI, JIM,              
          IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU.

1167
00:50:37,967 --> 00:50:40,500
       THANK YOU FOR TAKING CARE
       OF THE JOURNAL.          

1168
00:50:46,342 --> 00:50:49,376
I'M SO GLAD                     
TO HAVE FOUND YOU.              

1169
00:50:49,445 --> 00:50:50,811
        <i> THANKS TO JIM,</i>         

1170
00:50:50,879 --> 00:50:54,081
    <i> BILL MORAN'S THOUGHTS</i>      
  <i> ARE NOW FINALLY GOING HOME</i>   

1171
00:50:54,149 --> 00:50:56,416
       <i> TO THE DAUGHTER</i>         
        <i> HE NEVER KNEW.</i>         

1172
00:50:56,485 --> 00:51:00,320
I JUST FEEL LIKE I KNOW         
SO MUCH ABOUT YOU ALREADY.      

1173
00:51:00,389 --> 00:51:02,222
[ clears throat ]               
EXCUSE ME.                      

1174
00:51:10,199 --> 00:51:11,331
    SORRY.                      

1175
00:51:11,400 --> 00:51:14,501
THE DIARY'S BEEN IN OUR FAMILY  
FOR 63 YEARS.                   

1176
00:51:14,570 --> 00:51:18,105
WHAT WAS SO FASCINATING         
WAS READING IN THE DIARY        

1177
00:51:18,173 --> 00:51:21,141
ABOUT YOUR MOTHER               
CARRYING YOU                    

1178
00:51:21,210 --> 00:51:24,144
AND YOUR DAD BEING              
SO HAPPY AND EXCITED            

1179
00:51:24,213 --> 00:51:27,314
ABOUT YOUR MOM                  
BEING PREGNANT.                 

1180
00:51:27,383 --> 00:51:30,183
IN THE DIARY ITSELF,            
IT JUST COMES THROUGH           

1181
00:51:30,252 --> 00:51:34,688
THAT HE LOVES YOUR MOTHER       
VERY MUCH.                      

1182
00:51:34,757 --> 00:51:36,757
 <i> MORAN AND HIS FELLOW PILOTS</i>   

1183
00:51:36,825 --> 00:51:40,227
   <i> HAD HELPED DEAL HITLER'S</i>    
<i> WAR MACHINE A CRIPPLING BLOW,</i>  

1184
00:51:40,295 --> 00:51:42,896
      <i> AND THEIR CHILDREN</i>       
   <i> AND CHILDREN'S CHILDREN</i>     

1185
00:51:42,965 --> 00:51:45,699
    <i> WOULD LIVE IN A WORLD</i>      
    <i> THEY HAD TRANSFORMED.</i>      

1186
00:51:45,768 --> 00:51:49,403
THIS IS A GLIMPSE               
INTO YOUR FATHER'S LIFE.        

1187
00:51:49,471 --> 00:51:52,506
       THANK YOU VERY MUCH, JIM,
       FOR TREASURING IT        

1188
00:51:52,574 --> 00:51:55,208
           AND TAKING CARE OF IT
           FOR ALL THOSE YEARS. 

1189
